(1012, 'Personally I rather look forward to a computer program winning the world chess championship. Humanity needs a lesson in humility.', 'Richard Dawkins', 'computers'),
(1013, 'Computers may save time but they sure waste a lot of paper. About 98 percent of everything printed out by a computer is garbage that no one ever reads.', 'Andy Rooney', 'computers'),
