(1015, 'Never trust a computer you can\'t throw out a window.', 'Steve Wozniak', 'computers'),
(1016, 'The computer is a moron.', 'Peter Drucker', 'computers'),
(1017, 'Treat your password like your toothbrush. Don\'t let anybody else use it and get a new one every six months.', 'Clifford Stoll', 'computers'),
(1018, 'I am thankful the most important key in history was invented. It\'s not the key to your house your car your boat your safety deposit box your bike lock or your private community. It\'s the key to order sanity and peace of mind. The key is \'Delete.\'', 'Elayne Boosler', 'computers'),
(1019, 'The real danger is not that computers will begin to think like men but that men will begin to think like computers.', 'Sydney J. Harris', 'computers'),
(1020, 'To err is human - and to blame it on a computer is even more so.', 'Robert Orben', 'computers'),
(1021, 'Home computers are being called upon to perform many new functions including the consumption of homework formerly eaten by the dog.', 'Doug Larson', 'computers'),
(1022, 'I am not the only person who uses his computer mainly for the purpose of diddling with his computer.', 'Dave Barry', 'computers'),
(1023, 'The Internet: transforming society and shaping the future through chat.', 'Dave Barry', 'computers'),
(1024, 'The basis of computer work is predicated on the idea that only the brain makes decisions and only the index finger does the work.', 'Brian Eno', 'computers'),
(1025, 'Think? Why think! We have computers to do that for us.', 'Jean Rostand', 'computers'),
(1026, 'No one ever said on their deathbed \'Gee I wish I had spent more time alone with my computer\'.', 'Danielle Berry', 'computers'),
(1027, 'I was afraid of the internet... because I couldn\'t type.', 'Jack Welch', 'computers'),
(1028, 'It\'s hardware that makes a machine fast. It\'s software that makes a fast machine slow.', 'Craig Bruce', 'computers'),
(1029, 'Many of our own people here in this country do not ask about computers telephones and television sets. They ask - when will we get a road to our village.', 'Thabo Mbeki', 'computers'),
(1030, 'It\'s been my policy to view the Internet not as an \'information highway\' but as an electronic asylum filled with babbling loonies.', 'Mike Royko', 'computers'),
