(1044, 'I happen to think that computers are the most important thing to happen to musicians since the invention of cat-gut which was a long time ago.', 'Robert Moog', 'computers'),
(1045, 'The power of the computer is starting to spread.', 'Bill Budge', 'computers'),
(1046, 'One of the most feared expressions in modern times is \'The computer is down.\'', 'Norman Ralph Augustine', 'computers'),
(1047, 'Access to computers and the Internet has become a basic need for education in our society.', 'Kent Conrad', 'computers'),
(1048, 'If you could utilize the resources of the end users\' computers you could do things much more efficiently.', 'Niklas Zennstrom', 'computers'),
(1049, 'In computing turning the obvious into the useful is a living definition of the word \'frustration\'.', 'Alan Perlis', 'computers'),
(1050, 'Nanotechnology will let us build computers that are incredibly powerful. We\'ll have more power in the volume of a sugar cube than exists in the entire world today.', 'Ralph Merkle', 'computers'),
