(1054, 'Modern people are only willing to believe in their computers while I believe in myself.', 'Alain Robert', 'computers'),
(1055, 'The question of whether a computer can think is no more interesting than the question of whether a submarine can swim.', 'Edsger Dijkstra', 'computers'),
(1056, 'Computers have virtually replaced tape recorders.', 'Tony Visconti', 'computers'),
(1057, 'The good news about computers is that they do what you tell them to do. The bad news is that they do what you tell them to do.', 'Ted Nelson', 'computers'),
(1058, 'We can do things that we never could before. Stop-motion lets you build tiny little worlds and computers make that world even more believable.', 'Nick Park', 'computers'),
