(1345, 'Though men are apt to flatter and exalt themselves with their great achievements yet these are in truth very often owing not so much to design as chance.', 'Francois de La Rochefoucauld', 'design'),
(1346, 'I did not direct my life. I didn\'t design it. I never made decisions. Things always came up and made them for me. That\'s what life is.', 'B. F. Skinner', 'design'),
(1347, 'Almost all quality improvement comes via simplification of design manufacturing... layout processes and procedures.', 'Tom Peters', 'design'),
