(2109, 'Facts are to the mind what food is to the body.', 'Edmund Burke', 'food'),
(2110, 'A city is a place where there is no need to wait for next week to get the answer to a question to taste the food of any country to find new voices to listen to and familiar ones to listen to again.', 'Margaret Mead', 'food'),
(2111, 'Men do not have to cook their food they do so for symbolic reasons to show they are men and not beasts.', 'Edmund Leach', 'food'),
