(2159, 'I\'ve often said that the most important thing you can give your children is wings. Because you\'re not gonna always be able to bring food to the nest. You\'re... sometimes... they\'re gonna have to be able to fly by themselves.', 'Elizabeth Edwards', 'food'),
(2160, 'What the mass media offers is not popular art but entertainment which is intended to be consumed like food forgotten and replaced by a new dish.', 'W. H. Auden', 'food'),
