(4551, 'It\'s harder to be funny if you\'re handsome than if you\'re very normal-looking. It\'s just more relatable. You\'re the underdog. I mean it\'s funny to see people struggle and you don\'t buy that Brad Pitt is struggling you know that guy could be the most skill', 'Jonah Hill', 'funny'),
(4552, 'It\'s funny because I never think of myself as Little Miss All-Together.', 'Courteney Cox', 'funny'),
(4553, 'When I was a kid I didn\'t feel like I fit in because - this is really silly and I probably shouldn\'t say it but I didn\'t think anything was funny. So I used to go home and literally cry to my mom and my step-dad at the time and I didn\'t think anything was', 'Courteney Cox', 'funny'),
(4554, 'I realized my family was funny because nobody ever wanted to leave our house.', 'Anthony Anderson', 'funny'),
(4555, 'You know what? I never really factor Hollywood into anything. I\'m a black actor so I can\'t really control what Hollywood thinks. I gotta go do my thing and my jokes have got to be funny. Whatever I do has got to be great.', 'Jamie Foxx', 'funny'),
(4556, 'I really wanted to just be a musician. I didn\'t want to be anything else but I was funny and all that.', 'Jamie Foxx', 'funny'),
(4557, 'For years I used to bore my wife over lunch with stories about funny incidents.', 'James Herriot', 'funny'),
(4558, 'Movies these days have made killers into funny people. What\'s that all about? I\'ve got kids and family and friends and I don\'t like bad things. I don\'t think they\'re funny and it\'s irresponsible to make movies that don\'t show you how that\'s not good.', 'Billy Bob Thornton', 'funny'),
(4559, 'I tell you it\'s funny because the only time I think about HIV is when I have to take my medicine twice a day.', 'Magic Johnson', 'funny'),
(4560, 'A comedian\'s body is funny as well as his mind being funny his whole personage is funny.', 'Bobby Darin', 'funny'),
(4561, 'I want to be in \'Funny Girl.\' And I want Ryan Murphy to direct it.', 'Lea Michele', 'funny'),
(4562, 'It would be pretty funny to see a Beverly Hills white girl with mad rap skills.', 'Tori Spelling', 'funny'),
(4563, 'Being a funny person does an awful lot of things to you. You feel that you mustn\'t get serious with people. They don\'t expect it from you and they don\'t want to see it. You\'re not entitled to be serious you\'re a clown.', 'Fanny Brice', 'funny'),
(4564, 'Comedy is not funny. Comedy is hard work and timing and lots and lots of rehearsals.', 'Larry Hagman', 'funny'),
(4565, 'That\'s why I like to get out there and get people to see the other side of Mitt and know us in a different reflection when you see the family and how funny he is with the boys and with the grandkids. And you know just what a super guy he is. That\'s part o', 'Ann Romney', 'funny'),
(4566, 'Funny is funny.', 'Don Rickles', 'funny'),
(4567, 'Memories are doing funny things to us.', 'Milos Forman', 'funny'),
(4568, 'My dad loved to laugh. He was very funny and very silly.', 'Mike Myers', 'funny'),
(4569, 'Europe is scooters. Europe is five young people on one bench sharing a chocolate bar. Their idea of entertainment and fun is so much different than ours which is exactly why a movie about them would be funny.', 'Mike Myers', 'funny'),
(4570, 'So that\'s why one of my rules of parody writing is that it\'s gotta be funny regardless of whether you know the source material. It has to work on its own merit.', 'Al Yankovic', 'funny'),
(4571, 'People never ask people doing serious music \'Do you ever think about doing funny music?\'', 'Al Yankovic', 'funny'),
(4572, 'I\'ve never really understood that. It\'s a funny thing people sometimes accuse us of condescending to our characters somehow-that to me is kind of inexplicable.', 'Joel Coen', 'funny'),
(4573, 'Ninety-eight per cent of laughter is nothing to do with jokes which do not deserve to bear the weight of all the funny stuff in the world.', 'Arthur Smith', 'funny'),
(4574, 'The history of the relationship between comedy and swimming is short indeed. Of course it is always funny when someone falls into water but that\'s about it.', 'Arthur Smith', 'funny'),
(4575, '\'Married with Children\' was racy. It was sexist. It was a lot of things but mostly it was funny.', 'Katey Sagal', 'funny'),
(4576, 'My mother was a terrific force in my life. Wartime-generation woman hadn\'t gone to university but should have done. Was very funny very verbal very clever very witty.', 'Ian Hislop', 'funny'),
(4577, 'I was doing sketches that were funny but socially irresponsible. I felt I was deliberately being encouraged and I was overwhelmed.', 'Dave Chappelle', 'funny'),
(4578, 'It\'s funny recently I\'ve started to notice people\'s impersonations of me and it\'s basically like a hyperactive child.', 'Dave Grohl', 'funny'),
(4579, 'It\'s funny I actually made poorer decisions when I sobered up then when I was screwed up.', 'Corey Feldman', 'funny'),
(4580, 'It\'s funny having the same name as someone. Me Emma Watson and Emma Stone the amount of times I\'ve been called Emma Watson or Emma Stone is so funny. It\'s just \'cause we\'re all named Emma. None of us look alike.', 'Emma Roberts', 'funny'),
(4581, 'I don\'t really have a type of guy I like. It\'s just like nice guys cute boys I mean ones that are funny.', 'Emma Roberts', 'funny'),
(4582, 'But I think Kiss Kiss Bang Bang really got that thing where if a movie reads really funny and then has some dramatic or violent or sinister stuff in it you can\'t forget that primarily it has to be even funnier than you read it or that other stuff doesn\'t ', 'Robert Downey Jr.', 'funny'),
(4583, 'I wish I could be as thin as Jessica Simpson. I think she looks gorgeous! I have had Jessica on my show several times and I can tell you that girl is genuine and funny with a great self-deprecating sense of humor.', 'Rachael Ray', 'funny'),
(4584, 'And at the time it is funny how you can look at something and say for example with my shoulder injury when it first happened I said this is the worst thing that could happen to me. Why me why now? Now I look back and say it was probably the best thing tha', 'Drew Brees', 'funny'),
(4585, 'I think we\'re the only jokeless show on television. I mean really we have no setups and no punch lines. It\'s not a joke show. There are funny lines and funny moments but again the comedy is born of the human experience and awkward pauses are a great part ', 'Rainn Wilson', 'funny'),
(4586, 'We\'ve got a bunch of new writers now who tell me they grew up watching The Simpsons. It\'s bizarre and they\'re writing some very funny stuff.', 'Matt Groening', 'funny'),
(4587, 'Sometimes people get mad at The Simpsons\' subversive story telling but there\'s another message in there which is a celebration of making wild funny stories.', 'Matt Groening', 'funny'),
(4588, 'I can always get better. A lot of my ex-girlfriends don\'t think I\'m funny.', 'Dane Cook', 'funny'),
(4589, 'I didn\'t plan to be the rude middle-class comedian. You write a certain type of joke that you find funny and mine happen to be often rude. Yes it\'s juvenile but that\'s me.', 'Jimmy Carr', 'funny'),
(4590, 'Only bad golfers are lucky. They\'re the ones bouncing balls off trees curbs turtles and cars. Good golfers have bad luck. When you hit the ball straight a funny bounce is bound to be unlucky.', 'Lee Trevino', 'funny'),
(4591, 'Music is more difficult - try naming a political band. The Dead Kennedys. The Dead Kennedys are political but they are more funny than they are political.', 'Thom Yorke', 'funny'),
(4592, 'We sit in a room for months trying to think of funny things.', 'David Walliams', 'funny'),
(4593, 'I love a smart well-written show and \'30 Rock\' well you can\'t get any better than that. Tina Fey poos funny. There\'s nothing that she does that isn\'t funny. That show is an example of how brilliant she is. It\'s so smart. They\'ve done some brilliant commen', 'Andy Cohen', 'funny'),
(4594, 'I am accusing him of stealing my best material he was a very funny man.', 'Frank Carson', 'funny'),
(4595, 'It\'s unbearable when someone changes around you. Just imagine that your life partner changes then it is difficult to cope with. Or your mother. Or your father. They were strong and now they\'re like a baby - it\'s not so funny.', 'Michael Haneke', 'funny'),
(4596, '\'Funny Games\' was conceived as a provocation. My other films are different. If people feel my other films are or respond to them as provocation then that\'s quite different. \'Funny Games\' is the only one of mine where my intention was to provoke the audien', 'Michael Haneke', 'funny'),
(4597, 'When I first envisioned \'Funny Games\' in the mid-1990s it was my intention to have an American audience watch the movie. It is a reaction to a certain American cinema its violence its naivety the way American cinema toys with human beings. In many America', 'Michael Haneke', 'funny'),
(4598, 'I have an inability to enjoy things but that\'s why we\'re in comedy. If we were happy we wouldn\'t be funny I guess.', 'Paul Feig', 'funny'),
(4599, 'For years it\'s driven me crazy that women don\'t have better roles especially in comedies. I know so many funny women but I always felt... misogynist streak is too strong a term - but a dismissiveness.', 'Paul Feig', 'funny'),
(4600, 'I love funny people and when I\'m with funny people or people who are amusing in their weirdness I love it. Because that to me is funny as opposed to someone who stops and says \'Hey let me tell you a joke.\'', 'Paul Feig', 'funny'),
(4601, 'What\'s so great about working with really funny women is that vanity comes second. Whatever makes it real and funny they\'re going to go for and it\'s just great.', 'Paul Feig', 'funny'),
(4602, 'What I don\'t like is when I see stuff that I know has had a lot of improv done or is playing around where there\'s no purpose to the scene other than to just be funny. What you don\'t want is funny scene funny scene funny scene and now here\'s the epiphany s', 'Paul Feig', 'funny'),
(4603, 'Women\'s humor seems to be a little more supportive. It\'s just kind of trying to make the other one laugh through funny voices and kind of talking about other people. I respond to that. I feel less like I\'m going to get beat up in a room full of women than', 'Paul Feig', 'funny'),
(4604, 'It\'s funny when people say you have sex appeal or call you the next Brad Pitt. I just laugh. I\'m not that. I don\'t want to be that.', 'Kellan Lutz', 'funny'),
(4605, 'By no means do I want to be a piece of meat for the rest of my career. It\'s funny when you get asked to do a talk show and then they follow it up with requesting you take your shirt off.', 'Kellan Lutz', 'funny'),
(4606, 'See I don\'t really go after girls. Most of the girlfriends I\'ve had have come after me. So it\'s really funny when girls get offended because I don\'t hit on them.', 'Kellan Lutz', 'funny'),
(4607, 'It\'s interesting that whenever I meet some of the other Bond girls I always have something in common and it is an interesting sorority. We all share about our Bonds. \'Did your Bond do that?\' \'Yes mine did!\' So it is quite funny conversations. We may as we', 'Jane Seymour', 'funny'),
(4608, 'You know Stephen says in the movies no one ever goes to the bathroom. They shave they brush their teeth. He goes right at this sort of funny taboo we have about the bathroom and he turned it into this nightmare you know your worst fear of what\'s in there.', 'Lawrence Kasdan', 'funny'),
(4609, 'Funny is an attitude.', 'Flip Wilson', 'funny'),
(4610, 'My main point is to be funny if I can slip a message in there fine.', 'Flip Wilson', 'funny'),
(4611, 'Things can be funny only when we are in fun. When we\'re \'dead earnest\' humor is the only thing that is dead.', 'Flip Wilson', 'funny'),
(4612, 'Funny is not a color. Being black is only good from the time you get from the curtain to the microphone.', 'Flip Wilson', 'funny'),
(4613, 'I don\'t believe that anybody has come to a conclusion on why something is funny. It\'s funny because it\'s ridiculous and it\'s ridiculous for different reasons at different times.', 'Jackie Mason', 'funny'),
(4614, 'There are so many funny women in the world and there has been for so many years so I\'ll be happy when people can just move on from that and things can just be \'comedies\' and not \'female\' or \'male\' and everyone gets an equal opportunity.', 'Kristen Wiig', 'funny'),
(4615, 'But if something funny happens I can\'t resist. I have to tell the people.', 'Kathy Griffin', 'funny'),
(4616, 'I would like to do something modern and possibly funny.', 'Dan Stevens', 'funny'),
(4617, 'I\'ve always enjoyed making people laugh. But in order for me to be funny I have to get ticked off about something.', 'Carl Hiaasen', 'funny'),
(4618, 'Everyone comes up to me saying \'Cooee Julie! Hello!\' as if I know them. Of course I don\'t bloody know them. Am I flummoxed by it? Sometimes. I think \'Ooh love go easy.\' For a time I did feel this pressure that I had to be funny but it passes.', 'Julie Walters', 'funny'),
(4619, 'Oh all the time when Victoria Wood and I did our series. There were people asking \'Can women be funny?\' People still ask that. It\'s like asking: \'Can women breathe in and out?\'', 'Julie Walters', 'funny'),
(4620, 'I was the little funny one. I felt I was the child among grown women.', 'Julie Walters', 'funny'),
(4621, 'It\'s a real primal thing watching someone get hurt. It\'s funny and accessible.', 'Johnny Knoxville', 'funny'),
(4622, 'It\'s a funny thing - when I\'m crazed with work spending time with my children relaxes me. Yet at the end of a long weekend with them the very thing I need to relax is a little work and time away from them!', 'Emily Giffin', 'funny'),
(4623, 'It\'s really funny because the same people who loved me as Stringer Bell were the same people that were watching \'Daddy\'s Little Girls\' literally in tears.', 'Idris Elba', 'funny'),
(4624, 'I had seen movies before that that had made me laugh but I had never seen anything even remotely close to as funny as Richard Pryor was just standing there talking.', 'Joe Rogan', 'funny');
INSERT INTO `citations` (`id`, `citation`, `auteur`, `theme`) VALUES
(4625, 'I wouldn\'t totally rule out doing Letterman or the Tonight Show if I had a set that I just happened to write that I thought was funny but was still appropriate for network censors. But I\'m not going to go out of my way.', 'Joe Rogan', 'funny'),
(4626, 'The audience changes every night. You\'re the same person. You have to speak your mind and do the stuff that you think is funny and makes you laugh.', 'Joe Rogan', 'funny'),
(4627, 'The misconception is that standup comics are always on. I don\'t know any really funny comics that are annoying and constantly trying to be funny all the time.', 'Joe Rogan', 'funny'),
(4628, 'I used to say I wanted somebody funny and intelligent but kindness is the most important quality in a man.', 'Cat Deeley', 'funny'),
(4629, 'The great thing is that the funny side of getting old is fuel for my comedy.', 'Steve Coogan', 'funny'),
(4630, 'I think it\'s always funny when you see kids do Shakespeare.', 'Steve Coogan', 'funny'),
(4631, 'But with comedy it\'s a simple premise. If it\'s funny people laugh. If it\'s not they don\'t.', 'Steve Coogan', 'funny'),
(4632, 'Hitchcock had a charm about him. He was very funny at times. He was incredibly brilliant in his field of suspense.', 'Tippi Hedren', 'funny'),
(4633, 'One lion thinks it\'s just hilarious to tackle us. He\'s very funny about it... and we always know when it will happen.', 'Tippi Hedren', 'funny'),
(4634, 'Working with Chaplin was very amusing and strange. His films are so funny but working with him I found him to be a very serious man. Whereas the films of Hitchcock are macabre he could be a very funny man to work with always telling jokes and holding cour', 'Tippi Hedren', 'funny'),
(4635, 'I actually find novels that are determined to be funny at every turn quite oppressive.', 'Ian Mcewan', 'funny'),
(4636, 'It\'s funny though with films because you can incorporate a variety of elements and sometimes that can work for you and sometimes I think it can work against you.', 'Guy Pearce', 'funny'),
(4637, 'Comedians don\'t laugh. They\'re too busy analyzing why it\'s funny or not.', 'James Lipton', 'funny'),
(4638, 'What was really funny is that as I got older all those guys who called me a sissy in junior high school wanted me to be their best friend because they wanted to meet all the girls that I knew in figure skating.', 'Scott Hamilton', 'funny'),
(4639, 'I can\'t not find humor in elements of most parts of life but at the same time nothing ever seems perpetually funny to me.', 'Greg Kinnear', 'funny'),
(4640, 'And in a funny way each death is different and you mourn each death differently and each death brings back the death you mourned earlier and you get into a bit of a pile-up.', 'Nigella Lawson', 'funny'),
(4641, 'Also in a funny way if you have been happily married there are no unresolved areas nothing to prove to yourself after the other dies.', 'Nigella Lawson', 'funny'),
(4642, 'People often ask me how I make things funny. I don\'t make things funny.', 'Richard Russo', 'funny'),
(4643, 'If you work at comedy too laboriously you can kill what\'s funny in the joke.', 'Richard Russo', 'funny'),
(4644, 'For some reason and I don\'t know why but I don\'t think that I\'m funny in California. So I always want to do my movies east somewhere.', 'Kevin James', 'funny'),
(4645, 'I took \'P.S. I Love You\' thinking it was going to be a little funny and I ended up crying every day on that film.', 'Hilary Swank', 'funny'),
(4646, 'I think \'Saturday Night Live\' starting in the 1970s really gave women an outlet to be funny. A lot of those women went on to have film careers from Kristen Wiig now to Tina Fey and Gilda Radner.', 'Emma Stone', 'funny'),
(4647, 'I write about wounds the eternal treasons of life. It\'s not very funny but it\'s sincere. My commitment is to sincerity.', 'Tahar Ben Jelloun', 'funny'),
(4648, 'When I was doing ensemble theater and comedy work I felt I had some talents. But when I started doing my shows in Berkeley and found that I could be funny on my own I was shocked.', 'Whoopi Goldberg', 'funny'),
(4649, 'Memory is funny. Once you hit a vein the problem is not how to remember but how to control the flow.', 'Tobias Wolff', 'funny'),
(4650, 'People just don\'t laugh when their family is violated and you don\'t shrug it off. You band together and you defend together. It\'s a funny primitive instinct.', 'Phillip Noyce', 'funny'),
(4651, 'There\'s always something funny about men chasing women.', 'David Spade', 'funny'),
(4652, 'I don\'t know who the hell Paul Lynde is or why he\'s funny and I prefer it to be a mystery to me.', 'Paul Lynde', 'funny'),
(4653, 'Politicians... talk in generalities and lies and I think they\'ve caused all our grief. They\'re so awful they\'re really funny. I hate thinking this because my dad loved politics.', 'Paul Lynde', 'funny'),
(4654, 'As soon as I realized you could be funny as a job that was the job I wanted.', 'Seth Rogen', 'funny'),
(4655, 'I think when you do comedy you play by a different set of rules. No one really wants you to be in that good shape. Being in good shape implies a level of vanity that isn\'t necessarily funny.', 'Seth Rogen', 'funny'),
(4656, 'To me what separates a funny movie from a good movie is something personal.', 'Seth Rogen', 'funny'),
(4657, 'I can\'t watch other people doing comedy. As soon as somebody starts being funny I have to turn off because it upsets me. I get comedy indigestion. I just hate anybody else being funny. That\'s my job.', 'Jenny Eclair', 'funny'),
(4658, 'As a five-year-old in Berlin in 1965 I didn\'t know that funny women existed. It wasn\'t until I got back to England that I realised women could be funny.', 'Jenny Eclair', 'funny'),
(4659, 'Leno Conan. They are both really funny. They really know how to land one.', 'Jimmy Fallon', 'funny'),
(4660, 'Straight men just can\'t imagine the bliss of being in a relationship with someone who finds farting as funny as they do.', 'Graham Norton', 'funny'),
(4661, 'We live in a funny time. If you don\'t go corporate you can\'t compete. You\'re relegated as irrelevant. People used to admire that.', 'Ethan Hawke', 'funny'),
(4662, 'You can\'t teach somebody how to be funny. You\'re either funny or you ain\'t.', 'Denis Leary', 'funny'),
(4663, 'The things that make me angry still make me angry. George Carlin is 67 and he\'s still as funny as he\'s ever been and he\'s still angry. And that makes me feel good because I feel like if I stick around long enough I\'ll still be able to work.', 'Denis Leary', 'funny'),
(4664, 'The fact that the Kardashians could be more popular than a show like \'Mad Men\' is disgusting. It\'s a super disgusting part of our culture but I still find it funny to make a joke about it.', 'Jonah Hill', 'funny'),
(4665, '\'Funny People\' is my favorite performance of myself to date. Even though it\'s a comedy and there are serious moments I really felt like Leo felt like a real person. It didn\'t feel like I was playing myself. Whether it\'s a comedy or drama I just try to mak', 'Jonah Hill', 'funny'),
(4666, 'I don\'t want to be the one to break it to you but the future ain\'t that funny.', 'Albert Brooks', 'funny'),
(4667, 'Twitter to me works if you\'re funny. Twitter doesn\'t work as a promotional tool unless you do it very very very occasionally.', 'Albert Brooks', 'funny'),
(4668, 'I\'ve been to many funerals of funny people and they\'re some of the funniest days you\'ll ever have because the emotions run high.', 'Albert Brooks', 'funny'),
(4669, 'I think a lot of times on TV we see caricatures - that\'s what\'s funny.', 'Mayim Bialik', 'funny'),
(4670, 'I love being a dad it keeps me fit and inspired and children are so funny. They always supply you with acting material!', 'Wesley Snipes', 'funny'),
(4671, 'It\'s funny how most activists are pacifists.', 'Craig Bruce', 'funny'),
(4672, 'I\'ve always been part of comedy. One of the things about our family was that if we were reasonably funny with each other particularly my two brothers and myself when my father was upset with something you\'d want to make sure in some way you made him laugh', 'Leslie Nielsen', 'funny'),
(4673, 'So what I do now is to pre-empt that by making the up into a virtue and telling funny stories about how crap I am before people have a chance to notice it for themselves and think maybe I haven\'t realised.', 'Emily Mortimer', 'funny'),
(4674, 'If you think something\'s funny go with that. Most comedians pull jokes from a place of honesty.', 'Olivia Munn', 'funny'),
(4675, 'Funny is funny is funny.', 'Bob Newhart', 'funny'),
(4676, 'I really don\'t know what makes a comedian. I think it\'s a family background and environment. Yet if you put the same ingredients in another person he may never utter a funny line.', 'Bob Newhart', 'funny'),
(4677, 'You can go to a play that is enjoyable because it\'s funny and then on the next night you can go to a play that\'s enjoyable because it\'s \'disturbing.\'', 'Wallace Shawn', 'funny'),
(4678, 'I don\'t happen to have a sense of humor personally so I don\'t know what\'s funny about a character... This happens to be a feature of my life generally.', 'Wallace Shawn', 'funny'),
(4679, 'I was making my living from a joke about my appearance that I didn\'t understand and in a way still don\'t because when I look in a mirror it doesn\'t seem funny to me.', 'Wallace Shawn', 'funny'),
(4680, 'For some reason people find me funny. It\'s quite hard to define why a thought is funny. It\'s even harder to define why a person would be funny. It\'s a word that I can\'t define at all. But whether I know quite what it is or not I seem to be it.', 'Wallace Shawn', 'funny'),
(4681, 'We all know funny people who can\'t get it down on the page - even funny writers who can\'t get it down on the page.', 'Calvin Trillin', 'funny'),
(4682, 'If it\'s inappropriate to write about if there\'s nothing funny about it then it\'s not funny.', 'Calvin Trillin', 'funny'),
(4683, 'It\'s funny how a chubby kid can just be having fun and people call it entertainment!', 'Garth Brooks', 'funny'),
(4684, 'Sometimes comics will make the observation that it\'s not jokes that are funny it\'s characters that are funny. And isn\'t that true! That\'s why I always kill jokes. I\'m terrible at them because I get the joke right but I can\'t get the character right and it', 'David Mitchell', 'funny'),
(4685, 'I would call it a comedy variety show. We have some people just doing straight standup. We usually try to have one musical act of sort. So its just people being funny in different ways not just sketch not just standup not just characters all of those thin', 'Todd Barry', 'funny'),
(4686, 'Animals are sentient intelligent perceptive funny and entertaining. We owe them a duty of care as we do to children.', 'Michael Morpurgo', 'funny'),
(4687, 'Strange questions are the more interesting ones. Children by and large don\'t try to trip you up... they want to find out how you do this funny thing that you do... if they\'ve loved a story they love to know how it started.', 'Michael Morpurgo', 'funny'),
(4688, 'It\'s so funny because right now I\'m very tired and my brains a little dead I tend to get very focused and serious. So I\'m probably coming off a lot more like Scully right now.', 'Gillian Anderson', 'funny'),
(4689, 'I tend to play characters that I can infuse with certain kinds of humour. Even the baddest guy can be funny in his own particular way. I want the audience to engage with the character on some deeper level so that they leave the cinema still thinking about', 'Samuel L. Jackson', 'funny'),
(4690, 'It\'s a required part of your film history to know who Woody is. His movies are so wonderful and not just funny but so insightful about human behavior.', 'Scarlett Johansson', 'funny'),
(4691, 'I have no idea what I\'m going to say when I stand up to give a toast. But I do know that anything I say I find funny.', 'Don Rickles', 'funny'),
(4692, 'You know what\'s funny to me? Attitude.', 'Don Rickles', 'funny'),
(4693, 'Some people say funny things but I say things funny.', 'Don Rickles', 'funny'),
(4694, 'We are supposed to enjoy the good stuff now while we can with the people we love. Life has a funny way of teaching us that lesson over and over again.', 'Sheena Easton', 'funny'),
(4695, 'I also think if you\'re an actor and you can improvise when you go on an audition and you can improvise you\'re just a genius. If you can you know take a Tide commercial and you can just say one funny line that\'s not in the commercial they think you\'re a ge', 'Amy Poehler', 'funny'),
(4696, 'Most of the gaffes I\'ve made have not been funny - they\'ve been stupid.', 'Jim Lehrer', 'funny'),
(4697, 'My little dog he did not get ill. It is so funny that people get ill on a boat and dogs do not.', 'Anna Held', 'funny'),
(4698, 'Who knew Rob Lowe was funny? On \'Parks and Rec\' we\'ve got some of the funniest comedy writers some of the funniest comedians in the world working there. And if anything we don\'t just effuse to one another and be like \'Oh Rob Lowe\'s really funny\' if he was', 'Chris Pratt', 'funny'),
(4699, 'The American audience has really opened up to women being A.) funny and B.) kinda crude. \'Bridesmaids\' is R-rated and I think it was a major coup for women to have an R-rated comedy that did really well. Same as \'Bad Teacher.\'', 'Chris Pratt', 'funny'),
(4700, 'It\'s interesting - I always thought when I was doing more melodramatic stuff like \'Everwood\' that the directors were constantly reeling me in and stopping me from being funny.', 'Chris Pratt', 'funny'),
(4701, 'The key is just to ignore the pain because physical comedy only works if you see someone get hurt and they aren\'t actually hurt. If someone gets hit in the face with a bat falls down and gets back up it\'s funny. If they stay down and their jaw is wired sh', 'Chris Pratt', 'funny'),
(4702, 'It\'s a funny relationship that makeup artists have. I always feel kind of like a dentist. People look at me and think of pain.', 'Rick Baker', 'funny'),
(4703, 'I love Charlie Billy Burke\'s character. Writing for him is so spectacular he\'s so funny and wry and every scene he\'s in he just takes. There\'s a scene in \'Eclipse\' where Bella tells him she\'s a virgin and it\'s the funniest most awkward scene I\'ve ever see', 'Melissa Rosenberg', 'funny'),
(4704, 'It\'s funny how I use social media because I don\'t use it to promote my restaurants that much. I use it for social issues and I think that\'s what it\'s for. I do a few things - I mess around with music a lot because that\'s a passion of mine. If something st', 'Tom Colicchio', 'funny'),
(4705, 'He is very dry but also very funny... I think people tend to feel odd when I do my act. Unless you are an ironic person it\'s not a good place for you to be.', 'Colin Quinn', 'funny'),
(4706, 'You know the funny thing about Lorne and that show is that you can go over one million things but in a business of bean counters he still likes to laugh at small things and creates a show around it.', 'Colin Quinn', 'funny'),
(4707, 'Everybody\'s funny in different ways.', 'Colin Quinn', 'funny'),
(4708, 'Marie Antoinette was funny I\'m sure she was just misinterpreted. You know the \'Let them eat cake\' line. She seems like she was kind of funny like a Chelsea Handler or Kathy Griffin type.', 'Colin Quinn', 'funny'),
(4709, 'You can\'t make everybody laugh. You gotta just do what you think is funny. Just be obstreperous to everybody.', 'Colin Quinn', 'funny'),
(4710, 'You know how it is with writing. You just write what you want to write. There\'s no way to predict what is good or bad. You just do what you think is funny and either it works or you\'re finished. It\'s impossible to predict anything.', 'Colin Quinn', 'funny'),
(4711, 'I\'ve dated some women who have turned me on to some funny things that are strange for men to actually do but these things have become part of my process. I think the things I do for my appearance help make me look better. I even colour my hair because I l', 'Ryan Seacrest', 'funny'),
(4712, 'I\'m terrible at practical jokes. I do them too well so they\'re not funny. I end up saying \'Oh no I\'m joking I\'m joking.\'', 'Anna Torv', 'funny'),
(4713, 'Everybody\'s funny if you love them.', 'Anna Torv', 'funny'),
(4714, 'People don\'t realize that I\'m really funny and I\'m an excellent bridge player.', 'Sheryl Crow', 'funny'),
(4715, 'People say funny things all the time during really serious moments in life.', 'Mark Ruffalo', 'funny'),
(4716, 'I had a very funny family.', 'Zach Braff', 'funny'),
(4717, 'I think I would say \'The King\'s Speech\' is surprisingly funny in fact the audiences in London Toronto LA New York commented there\'s more laughter in this film than in most comedies while it is also a moving tear-jerker with an uplifting ending.', 'Tom Hooper', 'funny'),
(4718, 'The funny thing is that I write and I act a lot about being Jewish but I don\'t really think about it as a regular person.', 'Liev Schreiber', 'funny'),
(4719, 'It\'s funny when people talk about the 70s I can tell you the year of every album but when it comes to the later efforts I can\'t remember the exact years it\'s funny isn\'t it?', 'Steve Hackett', 'funny'),
(4720, 'I\'ve always found it easier to be funny than to be serious.', 'Molly Ivins', 'funny'),
(4721, 'And the funny thing is I\'ve always been an optimist - it\'s practically a congenital disorder with me.', 'Molly Ivins', 'funny'),
(4722, 'It\'s funny how intimate it feels to get a text.', 'Sophie Ellis Bextor', 'funny'),
(4723, 'I knew exactly what to do on Alien it was funny.', 'Ridley Scott', 'funny'),
(4724, 'I come more to Scotland than I ever used to so I feel more connected to it more part of the zeitgeist. You know when you realize you have a choice and I\'m choosing my homeland. It\'s funny: when you get older these things creep up to you.', 'Alan Cumming', 'funny'),
(4725, 'It\'s funny because when you\'re younger you\'re in a rush to be 18 or 21 or whatever. But then you hit 30. And now the days go by like hours. You think40 man this could be the halfway point. It could be the three-quarters point you know? Who knows?', 'Mark Wahlberg', 'funny'),
(4726, 'I\'m one of those hovering mothers and I know it\'s really important to have an independent child so I\'m trying to back off but it\'s hard. I love him so much and he\'s so funny and cute to me.', 'Selma Blair', 'funny'),
(4727, 'I actually was class clown but I don\'t know how that happened because I\'ve never been considered an outwardly funny person-as the people in this room will attest.', 'Janeane Garofalo', 'funny'),
(4728, 'I actually was class clown but I don\'t know how that happened because I\'ve never been considered an outwardly funny person.', 'Janeane Garofalo', 'funny'),
(4729, 'Comedy is surprises so if you\'re intending to make somebody laugh and they don\'t laugh that\'s funny.', 'Norm MacDonald', 'funny'),
(4730, 'Scream was great for what it was. For a horror film it was intelligent it was funny it took a laugh at itself.', 'Neve Campbell', 'funny'),
(4731, 'When I was a kid I wanted to be serious like Daniel Day-Lewis. No one really dreams of being a comic actor do they? Now I realise how stupid that is - and it\'s because comic acting isn\'t taken seriously enough. It\'s a discipline. You know instantly - eith', 'Chris O\'Dowd', 'funny'),
(4732, 'I think there\'s something in the fact that it\'s hard to be good looking and funny. You have to have an oddball quality people have to sympathise with you to find you funny.', 'Chris O\'Dowd', 'funny'),
(4733, 'One of the things I like about acting is that in a funny way I come back to myself.', 'Bill Murray', 'funny'),
(4734, 'For a Catholic kid in parochial school the only way to survive the beatings - by classmates not the nuns - was to be the funny guy.', 'George A. Romero', 'funny'),
(4735, 'It\'s sort of an action flick. You can\'t be that funny trying to steal diamonds.', 'Anthony Anderson', 'funny'),
(4736, 'I do find comedy difficult. I don\'t know why. Maybe I think about it too much. There\'s a tremendous amount of pressure to be funny.', 'Michelle Pfeiffer', 'funny'),
(4737, 'I think sometimes my humor is extremely dry and a lot of times I would say things that I thought were very funny but... I have a reputation of - people think of me as a very fundamentalist humorless fellow.', 'Ian MacKaye', 'funny'),
(4738, 'I don\'t dismiss the music that I was involved with I don\'t think it was a joke I don\'t think it was funny or a phase I don\'t think it was just something I was doing back then to me it was who I am. It connects all the way through. I don\'t distance myself ', 'Ian MacKaye', 'funny'),
(4739, 'Even as a kid I was never the generator of humor but I always knew who was funny who to hang out with.', 'Andrew Stanton', 'funny'),
(4740, 'In Italy I had an Afro and a lot of the kids came up and felt my hair. It really was funny. I wish I had understood Italian.', 'Sugar Ray Leonard', 'funny'),
(4741, 'I think a lot comes from having the experience of doing stand-up comedy. It allows you to figure out the psychology of an audience what things are funny and not.', 'Keenen Ivory Wayans', 'funny'),
(4742, 'Life is funny and it is interesting how we make it as serious as possible.', 'Elisha Cuthbert', 'funny'),
(4743, 'It\'s funny though speaking of fathers and sons because me and John Goodman played father and son like five or six years ago in the film \'Death Sentence\' and I got back with him again in \'Inside Llewyn Davis.\'', 'Garrett Hedlund', 'funny'),
(4744, 'It\'s funny that I got to do \'On the Road\' because the thing that had the biggest impact on me growing up was reading books. I was very inspired by the book and this spirit of Dean Moriarty and how envious we all are of somebody who can be that carefree.', 'Garrett Hedlund', 'funny'),
(4745, 'It\'s funny - I read that women look to chiseled-faced guys for one-night stands and to round-faced guys for marriage. When I\'m rounder in the face I like to say \'This is my long-term look.\' Or \'This is my wife-and-kids look right here.\'', 'Garrett Hedlund', 'funny'),
(4746, 'This is the great thing about Northern Ireland. I walk down the street and people stop me and say things like \'I know you. You\'re that wee golfer aren\'t you?\' I say \'Yeah that\'s me.\' They say \'Keep it up wee man.\' It\'s very funny and that\'s why I want to ', 'Rory McIlroy', 'funny'),
(4747, 'I have an all-Japanese design team and none of them speak English. So it\'s often funny and surprising how my ideas end up lost in translation.', 'Pharrell Williams', 'funny'),
(4748, 'The most important thing is to write material that YOU think is funny. If you don\'t think it\'s funny but you\'re convinced that other people will think it is well they won\'t.', 'Mo Rocca', 'funny'),
(4749, 'When it comes to war we focus more on the mainstream coverage of the event rather than the event itself. People dying is never funny. Protest puppets are always funny.', 'Mo Rocca', 'funny'),
(4750, 'I think that Obama is very cool. And I think he\'s clever and I think he can be witty. But I don\'t think he\'s funny in either the way that Reagan was funny - or John McCain and Dick Cheney are both funny in that ruthless kind of mean way.', 'Mo Rocca', 'funny'),
(4751, 'We want to be funny. We want to make people laugh... We\'ll do whatever it takes.', 'Colin Mochrie', 'funny'),
(4752, 'But sooner or later I\'d love to do a comedy. I mean I think that you know people don\'t think that that\'s in my wheelhouse because I\'ve sort of played a lot of dramatic stuff and that\'s certainly a side of myself that I want at some point in the right cont', 'Matthew Fox', 'funny'),
(4753, 'I love nerds. Comic-Con junkies are the tastemakers of tomorrow. Isn\'t that funny? The tables have turned.', 'Kristen Bell', 'funny'),
(4754, 'I think the Cold War works as a great analogy or simile for different kinds of conflict. It\'s funny when you look back at it it\'s one of the last times that the boundaries were clear. Now as we see on \'Homeland\' there are no clear boundaries and enemies.', 'Matthew Rhys', 'funny'),
(4755, 'I always just wanted to be funny. I never really planned to be scary.', 'R. L. Stine', 'funny'),
(4756, 'I started writing when I was 9 years old. I was like this weird kid who would just stay in my room typing little funny magazines and drawing comic strips.', 'R. L. Stine', 'funny'),
(4757, 'The token gay character is always so funny and so fantastic. That\'s happened a lot. Or they\'re often purely victims.', 'Ezra Miller', 'funny'),
(4758, 'You can\'t be funny if you don\'t have good material.', 'Matt LeBlanc', 'funny'),
(4759, 'I have funny bones. If there\'s ever any kind of tension I\'ll always be the one to try and be funny to loosen things up.', 'Matt LeBlanc', 'funny'),
(4760, 'It\'s funny - nowadays people that are famous get chased by paparazzi. They have this fame but they don\'t have the money to hide from it.', 'Matt LeBlanc', 'funny'),
(4761, 'Being funny with a funny voice is more my comfort zone a broader character that I try to humanize a kind of silly or wacky persona that I try to fill in.', 'Hank Azaria', 'funny'),
(4762, 'You can\'t be funny for funny\'s sake. You try to get as outrageous situation as you can but it always has to be believable and based in real character motivations and what people would really do.', 'Hank Azaria', 'funny'),
(4763, 'It\'s funny because I sometimes feel that I\'m most creative when I\'m pregnant.', 'Georgina Chapman', 'funny'),
(4764, 'Johnny Rotten. He\'s a big fan of mine. I used to see him out in the audience in England and he\'d stand up and holler. He\'s funny. Smart too and a nice guy. Don\'t think he\'s a jerk because he isn\'t.', 'Don Van Vliet', 'funny'),
(4765, 'If people want to compete for leadership of a religious group they can compete in piety. A chilling thought. Or funny.', 'Mary Douglas', 'funny'),
(4766, 'Back in the \'70s like one of my favorite movies ever was \'The Bad News Bears\' and that was a kids\' movie but I don\'t think of it that way. I think of it as just a great movie because Walter Matthau was so funny and so harsh with those kids.', 'Jack Black', 'funny'),
(4767, 'I just couldn\'t go back to Suddenly Susan after David Strickland\'s suicide. I didn\'t see how we could make the show light and funny any more.', 'Judd Nelson', 'funny'),
(4768, 'It\'s funny now how much we look at - whatever you want to call it: art design culture stuff film - online and how in the online world you\'re instantly global.', 'Mike Mills', 'funny'),
(4769, 'One can always come up with funny lists and jokes. You know what? I take it back. Not everyone can always come up with funny lists and some jokes. I\'m very lucky to have a gift where I can do that pretty ably.', 'John Hodgman', 'funny'),
(4770, 'People forget how outcast \'They Might Be Giants\' can be. They have a reputation for writing really deft funny clever melodies and they also make a lot of music for kids which is terrific but when you see them in concert they can rock the house.', 'John Hodgman', 'funny'),
(4771, 'It\'s so funny looking back but my so-called overnight success actually took 15 years. I remember when I didn\'t have any money and my only car was mom\'s Hyundai.', 'Criss Angel', 'funny'),
(4772, 'Mmmm... the comedy that matters is the comedy you pull out of thin air. It\'s a bit like when something funny has happened and you try to explain it to someone else and end up saying \'You had to be there.\'', 'Jack Dee', 'funny'),
(4773, 'Plus I love comic writing. Nothing satisfies me more than finding a funny way to phrase something.', 'Michael Pollan', 'funny'),
(4774, 'It\'s funny because I\'m a man of strong opinions and when I make one I stand by it even if it starts to appear incorrect to me after a while.', 'Danny Bonaduce', 'funny'),
(4775, 'I think I have a dark view of the world. I have to make everything funny otherwise it all seems so sad.', 'Moon Unit Zappa', 'funny'),
(4776, 'It\'s sad and upsetting when you see somebody crying hysterically but at the same time it\'s real funny.', 'Seth Green', 'funny'),
(4777, 'Well in the book Carrie was my alter ego. In real life Sarah Jessica and I don\'t look anything alike. But people do say that we sound alike. Sarah Jessica is an adorable girl and she is very funny.', 'Candace Bushnell', 'funny'),
(4778, 'I think if actors don\'t think of themselves as funny in real life they think they can\'t do comedy.', 'Ben Barnes', 'funny'),
(4779, 'I joke around a lot about the manic times because they\'re funny. We manics do outrageous things and it is part of our colorful nature.', 'Patty Duke', 'funny'),
(4780, 'I like all Jim Carrey films. They\'re really funny.', 'Rupert Grint', 'funny'),
(4781, 'Yes I believe blue material is funny but if that\'s all you\'ve got you\'re dead in the water. It\'s not good.', 'Howard Stern', 'funny'),
(4782, 'I\'m not a very serious person. You know how they say that clowns are very funny in public and are really sad at home? I\'m really kind of stupid at home and more serious in public.', 'Roland Joffe', 'funny'),
(4783, 'It\'s funny because I did all of these interviews as soon as I had the baby and they were asking questions and I really didn\'t have an idea of anything because I was so blurry.', 'Emily Procter', 'funny'),
(4784, 'That\'s a funny thing fame. People definitely do treat you differently. When you begin to be successful people say \'Don\'t go changing.\' Well that\'s easy to say but the fact is you don\'t change at all - other people do.', 'Jonathan Rhys Meyers', 'funny'),
(4785, 'I tell girls all the time that the men that have fallen in love with me have all fallen during a man repeller stage... funny how life works out like that.', 'Rachel Roy', 'funny'),
(4786, 'I think it\'s really important for celebrities to use their power of money and fame to get their voices out there. It\'s funny to me that we\'re expected to keep quiet just because of who we are. Why do I lose my right to speak my mind because I\'m famous?', 'Lisa Edelstein', 'funny'),
(4787, 'I\'m not a movie guy I\'m not a TV sitcom guy but whatever seems to fit and is funny is good for me.', 'Dave Attell', 'funny'),
(4788, 'You have to understand the tone of the movie because if it\'s supposed to be funny it can be funny violent like the Home Alone stuff but you have to really understand the tone of what you\'re doing and make the action work for that and for the character.', 'David R. Ellis', 'funny'),
(4789, 'I really love \'Soapdish.\' I wish \'Soapdish\' had more of a moment because I felt that that is a really strong funny movie. Kevin Kline is hilarious in that movie.', 'Elisabeth Shue', 'funny'),
(4790, 'I don\'t know. I think it\'s funny! I think it\'s funny! I go what? It\'s so absurd. I\'m alone.', 'Danny DeVito', 'funny'),
(4791, 'It\'s funny that all these goths paint their faces with such white make-up and that is the actual colour of my skin I am that pale!', 'Kelly Osbourne', 'funny'),
(4792, 'To this day I\'ve found that it doesn\'t matter what a guy looks like if he\'s really funny. His sense of humor makes him attractive. On the other hand you don\'t hear men saying \'No she\'s not pretty but is she ever funny!\'', 'Catherine O\'Hara', 'funny'),
(4793, 'Everything seems fine until you\'re about 40. Then something is definitely beginning to go wrong. And you look in the mirror with your old habit of thinking \'While I accept that everyone grows old and dies it\'s a funny thing but I\'m an exception to that ru', 'Martin Amis', 'funny'),
(4794, 'It\'s funny but when I arrived in California to start college I was much more interested in becoming a surfer and cruise along in life from one beach to the next. I didn\'t plan out any huge career for myself.', 'Benicio Del Toro', 'funny'),
(4795, 'I was going through a little bit of turbulence in my career. And so it\'s funny how turbulence itself will make you hold onto something for security. And so the only thing I knew is trust in the Lord and lean not unto your own heart in all thy ways acknowl', 'Emmitt Smith', 'funny'),
(4796, 'I actually feel like for a lot of my career I wasn\'t able to show my comedic range. I did a lot of dramas and dramedies. I was on \'E.R.\' That\'s not generally thought of as a funny show.', 'Busy Philipps', 'funny'),
(4797, 'I have an older sister named Haley and she wanted to be an actress. So I wanted to be an actress. It\'s really funny the way that some people don\'t give kids enough credit for like really being driven and really wanting to do things so badly.', 'Hilary Duff', 'funny'),
(4798, 'If I\'m in something funny I like to try and find some kind of serious line in it that people can relate to.', 'Ron Livingston', 'funny'),
(4799, 'If you could cross a lion and a monkey that\'s what I\'d be because monkeys are funny and lions are strong.', 'Marlon Wayans', 'funny'),
(4800, 'I\'m good at coming up with wacky characters and funny dialogue.', 'Marlon Wayans', 'funny'),
(4801, 'Comedy clubs can be brutal. Those people are for real and if you aren\'t funny they aren\'t laughing. They don\'t care who you are.', 'Marlon Wayans', 'funny'),
(4802, 'Gotta stay in the gym stay funny stay sharp. I just love working.', 'Marlon Wayans', 'funny'),
(4803, 'I think it\'s actually a misperception that I am a comedic actress. I do more drama than comedy but very little of it has been seen. When you are in big funny movies and they do well and your little part in it kind of explodes people perceive you as a come', 'Octavia Spencer', 'funny'),
(4804, 'I don\'t think of myself as a comedian but as an artist a scientist and chemist who just happens to be funny. I started doing stand-up to add another level to my game. I feel that I\'m a young rookie with a veteran\'s skill.', 'Marlon Wayans', 'funny'),
(4805, 'I feel cheesy when I see \'Silver Spoons.\' Some of it was funny but some of it was just cheese! My kids love it but I look at it and cringe.', 'Ricky Schroder', 'funny'),
(4806, 'I\'ve got to get on myself to be sharp funny and loose.', 'David Spade', 'funny'),
(4807, 'Sometimes I am so dry that people don\'t know I\'m kidding and think I\'m being serious. I enjoy this because their reactions are often funny.', 'Robert Crais', 'funny'),
(4808, 'I would love to play \'Funny Girl\' or \'Evita\' but I idolize the women who have played those parts. I don\'t know if there needs to be another version of those shows.', 'Idina Menzel', 'funny'),
(4809, 'I understand a woman who validates herself by getting attention from the opposite sex. I have a friend who is that to a T... Doesn\'t mean she isn\'t a good person. That\'s a funny character to play.', 'Cheryl Hines', 'funny'),
(4810, 'At school I was very shy. I wasn\'t funny really.', 'Michel Gondry', 'funny'),
(4811, 'I love weird or funny or beautiful sentences Joy Williams could write a microwave-oven manual and I\'m sure I\'d love it because the sentences would be tuned up like music.', 'Karen Russell', 'funny'),
(4812, 'I remember listening to the radio as a kid and finding that the songs always made me feel more peaceful. Funny but the more hurtin\' the music was the better it made me feel. I think of that now when I write my songs. I may not be feelin\' the blues myself ', 'Chris Isaak', 'funny'),
(4813, 'What was funny if you were there is that we were all immensely sophisticated people who knew exactly what she was going to say and we\'re chatting away nice to see you.', 'Anthony Holden', 'funny'),
(4814, 'I\'m so unprofessional on set it\'s not even funny.', 'Katharine McPhee', 'funny'),
(4815, 'It\'s funny that it all becomes about clothes. It\'s bizarre. You work your butt off and then you win an award and it\'s all about your dress. You can\'t get away from it.', 'Reese Witherspoon', 'funny'),
(4816, 'I follow the most random people on Twitter. I follow famous people like Khloe Kardashian who surprisingly makes really funny tweets all the time.', 'Chloe Moretz', 'funny'),
(4817, 'I was not particularly bright I wasn\'t very athletic I was a little too tall odd funny looking I was just really weird as a kid.', 'Uma Thurman', 'funny'),
(4818, 'I think it\'s so funny when people think they can\'t control a movie star. They can. We\'re just women you know.', 'Esther Williams', 'funny'),
(4819, 'I always approach comedy roles pretending they aren\'t funny.', 'Brendan Fraser', 'funny'),
(4820, 'I feel funny about owning art. I don\'t really want to say: \'Wow come and see my Monet - it\'s in a dark room at the bottom of my cellar.\'', 'Baz Luhrmann', 'funny'),
(4821, 'I love Mikhail Bulgakov. He is very original and takes the story to unexpected places. I didn\'t realise political writing could be so funny.', 'Denise Mina', 'funny'),
(4822, 'And there\'s a visceral fun in watching Team America and making it like taking a puppet and throwing it against the wall. Because it\'s not CG there\'s something funny about it.', 'Matt Stone', 'funny'),
(4823, 'So often I read scripts and am like \'This would never happen in real life. It\'s not trying to be funny. It\'s trying to be serious.\'', 'Shailene Woodley', 'funny'),
(4824, 'Acting is all about big hair and funny props... All the great actors knew it. Olivier knew it Brando knew it.', 'Harold Ramis', 'funny'),
(4825, 'Billy Crystal knows how to make people laugh. He\'s got 30 years on stage... there\'s no telling him what\'s funny.', 'Harold Ramis', 'funny'),
(4826, 'I\'m not a believer in the pratfall. I don\'t think it\'s funny just to have someone fall down.', 'Harold Ramis', 'funny'),
(4827, 'They did that little thing on South Park and they mentioned my name and had a character of me judging a Halloween contest. It was really funny.That made me the coolest aunt on earth.', 'Tina Yothers', 'funny'),
(4828, 'There\'s a constant flow of child actors. It\'s kind of funny to watch the new crew come through. I think You poor little things. You\'re going to have to struggle for a long time.', 'Tina Yothers', 'funny'),
(4829, 'It\'s funny growing up there was never anybody around me with any kind of artistic bent.', 'Nick Offerman', 'funny'),
(4830, 'When I was in college I was in the theater department which for anyone who has been involved in any kind of theater program you know that it\'s really wacky and tight-knit a real family. Me and my good friends from college would do random shows and plays t', 'Darren Criss', 'funny'),
(4831, 'With Portlandia I don\'t think our intention is always to find something funny. Sometimes the humor comes from taking something really seriously. We\'re okay with making somebody feel uncomfortable or uneasy.', 'Carrie Brownstein', 'funny'),
(4832, 'I got to play with Nintendo\'s Wii yes it\'s a funny name and not very revolutionary but it was fun whipping your arms around.', 'Olivia Munn', 'funny'),
(4833, 'Jon Stewart hires people that he thinks are funny. That\'s it. That\'s the only requirement.', 'Olivia Munn', 'funny'),
(4834, 'It is possible in this world to be pretty and funny and successful all at the same time.', 'Olivia Munn', 'funny'),
(4835, 'I think it\'s always funny when somebody thinks you\'re going to do something super sexy and then you don\'t.', 'Olivia Munn', 'funny'),
(4836, 'Sometimes in the most tragic situation something just profoundly funny happens.', 'David Hyde Pierce', 'funny'),
(4837, 'And I think that being able to make people laugh and write a book that\'s funny makes the information go down a lot easier and it makes it a lot more fun to read easier to understand and often stronger. So there\'s all kinds of advantages to it.', 'Al Franken', 'funny'),
(4838, 'It is funny what a year can do.', 'Victor Cruz', 'funny'),
(4839, 'It\'s funny in a way the actor is a writer. It\'s not like the two things are so separate as to be like apples and oranges. The writer and the actor are one.', 'Sam Shepard', 'funny'),
(4840, 'Stealing you\'ll go far in life. Actually there is something funny about getting away with it.', 'Mike Judge', 'funny'),
(4841, 'Movies don\'t look hard but figuring it out getting the shape of it getting everybody\'s character right and having it be funny make sense and be romantic it\'s creating a puzzle. Yes having been a writer for so long I have an awareness of when things are go', 'Nancy Meyers', 'funny'),
(4842, 'I can do comedy so people want me to do that but the other side of comedy is depression. Deep deep depression is the flip side of comedy. Casting agents don\'t realize it but in order to be funny you have to have that other side.', 'Parker Posey', 'funny'),
(4843, 'What\'s funny is my husband doesn\'t have any tattoos at all so he must be the very conservative one.', 'Ashley Scott', 'funny'),
(4844, 'I watched a lot of silent directors who were absolutely great like John Ford and Fritz Lang Tod Browning and also some very modern directors like The Coen Brothers. The directors take the freedom within their own movies to be melodramatic or funny when th', 'Michel Hazanavicius', 'funny'),
(4845, 'What I fell in love with as a child was \'My Fair Lady\' \'Funny Face\' \'American in Paris\' and \'Singin\' in the Rain.\' Just perfect movies to me and I was dancing. I started ballet when I was three. And I fell in love with those movies and fell in love with A', 'Dianna Agron', 'funny'),
(4846, 'My job is mostly to entertain and be funny.', 'Rosie O\'Donnell', 'funny'),
(4847, 'Sometimes you have to take the focus off of you and put it on someone else and it\'s funny what you can accomplish and how much strength you really have.', 'Hoda Kotb', 'funny'),
(4848, 'I don\'t think I was funny until college. I lived with some Harvard MD/PhD students - they were so smart and what I contributed to the house was I was the funny one.', 'Wendy Liebman', 'funny'),
(4849, 'When I was younger I wanted to be a big movie star who\'d get to be funny on talk shows and then I wanted to retire and write science fiction.', 'Scott Thompson', 'funny'),
(4850, 'When you are not treated seriously you develop comically. Its sense of oneself is so fractured and fragile that it\'s like the picked-on kid who has to become funny.', 'Scott Thompson', 'funny'),
(4851, 'I got pregnant at 40 by surprise. It\'s funny because when we found out we were pregnant I said \'Okay let\'s experience that.\' You just have to just go with it because it\'s rare.', 'Julianna Margulies', 'funny'),
(4852, 'Billy is a funny cheeky lovely boy and I love being with him. Parenthood is terrifying though. I can barely walk past a building without panicking that it\'s going to collapse on his head.', 'Rufus Sewell', 'funny'),
(4853, 'The funny thing is the songs that people think are about me probably aren\'t. And the songs that are probably are the ones they wouldn\'t think... so that\'s where it kind of is funny.', 'LeAnn Rimes', 'funny'),
(4854, 'Funny I don\'t feel any more powerful today than yesterday.', 'Jerry B. Jenkins', 'funny'),
(4855, 'The Islam of the 18th 19th and first half of the 20th century was a poor thing. Nobody bothered about it. Islam was that funny sort of pure system of beliefs that depressed people in the Middle East held as their religion.', 'John Keegan', 'funny'),
(4856, 'Most of my ideas just come out funny.', 'Tim Heidecker', 'funny'),
(4857, 'Sometimes laughing isn\'t the best judge of what\'s funny \'cause I think there\'s a lot of things that are really funny that don\'t make you laugh that don\'t make you physically audibly make a noise but is something that is much more powerful than that.', 'Tim Heidecker', 'funny'),
(4858, 'There is nothing funny about a well-adjusted intelligent person making the right choices.', 'Tim Heidecker', 'funny'),
(4859, 'I\'m always in situations where you can\'t be funny and yet I want to do it anyway.', 'Tim Heidecker', 'funny'),
(4860, 'It\'s a funny thing about me. I don\'t have any interest in food most of the time now although when I was a kid I was always hungry.', 'Alan Ladd', 'funny'),
(4861, 'I wasn\'t even 20 at the time but it taught me something about drugs. They can take a good man a warm funny loving family man and turn him into a loser and worse.', 'Michael Bergin', 'funny'),
(4862, 'I believe in a funny way the job of the novelist is to be out there on the fringes and speaking for an experience that has not really been spoken for.', 'Donna Tartt', 'funny'),
(4863, 'Funny how moms can tell you what to do no matter how old or big you are.', 'Gabrielle Reece', 'funny'),
(4864, 'I didn\'t grow up identifying with beauty. I grew up thinking I could be smart and funny - those are the things I got feedback on.', 'Lauren Graham', 'funny'),
(4865, 'Inappropriateness is funny to me. Rudeness is hilarious.', 'Zach Galifianakis', 'funny'),
(4866, 'I think if they put a laugh track on \'Intervention\' it would be funny.', 'Zach Galifianakis', 'funny'),
(4867, 'We all know how funny Morrissey is. Actually you know what? I say that sarcastically. His songs are some of the funniest songs I\'ve ever heard in my life. I mean really. I mean not that the \'Girlfriend in a Coma\' is like really funny.', 'Zach Galifianakis', 'funny'),
(4868, 'When I was in high school I used to sit by myself in the cafeteria - not necessarily by choice - but I thought it was funny to talk to people that weren\'t there.', 'Zach Galifianakis', 'funny'),
(4869, 'Laughter is involuntary. If it\'s funny you laugh.', 'Tom Lehrer', 'funny'),
(4870, 'What\'s funny about that is when I was writing Twilight just for myself and not thinking of it as a book I was not thinking about publishing and yet at the same time I was casting it in my head. Because when I read books I see them very visually.', 'Stephenie Meyer', 'funny'),
(4871, 'I auditioned for a solo in church and got it. I was about seven and I sang a song called \'Jesus I Heard You Had a Big House\' and I remember people standing up at the end and me thinking \'Oh I think I\'m going to like this.\' That\'s how it all began. Sounds ', 'Kristin Chenoweth', 'funny'),
(4872, 'It\'s so different when you change your hair color you\'re treated so differently. It\'s a very funny experience. It\'s fun - I love changing up my hair.', 'Kate Bosworth', 'funny'),
(4873, 'I\'m a big fan of certain new acts. I love any genre of music and I think it\'s really great to see that there are new artists coming through. It\'s kinda funny to think that I\'m like the old man on campus now. But I\'m really happy for groups like One Direct', 'Joe Jonas', 'funny'),
(4874, 'When I turned about 12 or 13 I realised that being funny wasn\'t about remembering jokes. It was about creating them.', 'Paul Merton', 'funny'),
(4875, 'They\'re great girls. They\'re very funny they\'re very smart they\'re fun to be with. They\'re very lively as I think people can tell. And you know they\'re very confident girls.', 'Laura Bush', 'funny'),
(4876, 'And regardless of the fact that in this country certainly in the arts we treat comedy as a second-class citizen I\'ve never thought of it that way. I\'ve always thought it to be important. The last time I looked the Greeks were holding up two masks. I\'ve al', 'Jeff Daniels', 'funny'),
(4877, 'It\'s funny but we were living on this small island off the coast of Charleston South Carolina when I was 9.', 'Josh Lucas', 'funny'),
(4878, 'I have no agenda except to be funny. Neither I or the writers profess to offer any worldly wisdom.', 'Julia Louis-Dreyfus', 'funny'),
(4879, 'In my experience it\'s not just that serious books get a hearing on comedy shows. But serious books get a serious hearing as well as a funny one on comedy shows.', 'Michael Mandelbaum', 'funny'),
(4880, 'It\'s a bit like school camp shooting a film. Everyone\'s on heat. It\'s a strange energy. It\'s full of adrenalin. I funnel my excess energy in funny little ways. I do a lot of dancing in my trailer. I love music.', 'Alice Englert', 'funny'),
(4881, 'Here\'s the funny thing about the response I\'ve been aware of to my dating famous people: It\'s been very negative. I\'m either not good-looking enough not a good enough actor or not successful enough for these people.', 'Dax Shepard', 'funny'),
(4882, 'I like the hot-cold the sugar-salt being able to play over-the-top and dramatic things - in the same film. Just as in my life I can be very funny and at other times almost extinguished.', 'Jean Dujardin', 'funny'),
(4883, 'I\'m an off-road racecar driver. And I think every woman in my life has told me that\'s not a sensible hobby. But when I was growing even more than I wanted to be funny I wanted to be a racecar driver. That\'s all I thought about. I worked for a race team wh', 'Dax Shepard', 'funny'),
(4884, 'Kyle Baker\'s work is really funny but it\'s also got a very clear vision.', 'Bill Sienkiewicz', 'funny'),
(4885, 'It\'s funny: I\'ve been very successful and done a lot of films and I don\'t really have an agent - I don\'t really pursue jobs I let people come to me.', 'Rick Baker', 'funny'),
(4886, 'If you look at the game and everything it\'s not quite like looking at an animated film because that\'s total character. This this is really movement but it\'s got funny little things if you look for the humor. They\'re actually getting to the character.', 'Don Bluth', 'funny'),
(4887, 'It\'s a funny thing because you look at the careers of other filmmakers and you see them sort of slow down and you realize maybe this becomes harder to do as you get older. That\'s sort of a cautionary thing. I hope it doesn\'t happen to me.', 'Joel Coen', 'funny'),
(4888, 'There\'s a darkness under \'The Hangover\' because ultimately there\'s a missing person and it\'s not really that funny. There\'s a sort of darkness under it that I love and still people are laughing as hard if not harder than they did in \'Old School.\'', 'Todd Phillips', 'funny'),
(4889, 'I think people like comedies and I think concept driven comedies seem to be working when it\'s a clear concept and you deliver funny stuff.', 'Todd Phillips', 'funny');
INSERT INTO `citations` (`id`, `citation`, `auteur`, `theme`) VALUES
(4890, 'Now that I\'m more mature in a funny way I can even appreciate that I\'ve bad to become more aware of my body. Since I\'ve chosen acting as my career I have to keep my weight down anyway-I\'ve been used to it for years so it\'s no problem. And there\'s nothing ', 'Dana Hill', 'funny'),
(4891, 'Comedy is so subjective. You could be in a room with 400 people laughing at a joke and you could just not think it\'s funny. You\'re just sitting there like \'Am I in the twilight zone? Why is everyone laughing?\' It\'s such a personal thing. People have such ', 'Todd Phillips', 'funny'),
(4892, 'I would do it today because the thing that appealed to me was not necessarily the mechanics of the robot but it was his personality and how funny and charming he was.', 'John Badham', 'funny'),
(4893, 'You know if I started worrying about what the critics think I\'d never make another comedy. You couldn\'t pick a less funny group than critics - you couldn\'t find a more bitter group of people!', 'Todd Phillips', 'funny'),
(4894, 'When I was a kid I had this funny blonde hair and everyone called me \'Chick\' because I looked like Tweety Bird.', 'Nicky Hilton', 'funny'),
(4895, 'I think that \'Hangover II\' is as funny as \'The Hangover I\' honest to God but I think that it\'s a little bit darker and the stakes are a little bit higher.', 'Todd Phillips', 'funny'),
(4896, 'I don\'t think know if anything\'s going to translate anywhere. You\'re making a movie you hope it\'s going to be funny you can\'t think about how it\'s going to go over.', 'Ben Stiller', 'funny'),
(4897, 'If you can find the line between sympathetic and creepy you have reached a very funny area.', 'Jason Segel', 'funny'),
(4898, 'I don\'t think the public is dying to see me necessarily be funny all the time.', 'Ben Stiller', 'funny'),
(4899, 'I love New York. I was sad depressed and incredibly moved by our fellow countrymen and what they\'ve done. I wanted to give people a chance to see something funny have a distraction.', 'Ben Stiller', 'funny'),
(4900, 'Jim Carrey a comic genius has a harder time overcoming the public\'s desire for him to be funny simply because he\'s so good at it.', 'Ben Stiller', 'funny'),
(4901, 'If you take a bunch of superstars and put them in a room where they don\'t have their assistants and entourage it\'s funny to see what happens.', 'Daryl Hall', 'funny'),
(4902, 'Because death and illness are the most horrible things in life of course that\'s where the most absurdly funny things are going to happen.', 'Julia Sweeney', 'funny'),
(4903, 'I think one of the basic tasks in life - one of the nice things we can do for each other - is to take things that are horrible and scary and make them acceptable and less frightening and if possible funny. It feels great to succeed at that.', 'Julia Sweeney', 'funny'),
(4904, 'I appreciate humor so much but I\'m actually not a funny girl.', 'Emmanuelle Chriqui', 'funny'),
(4905, 'During the Great Depression when people laughed their worries disappeared. Audiences loved these funny men. I decided to become one.', 'Jerry Stiller', 'funny'),
(4906, 'I remember interviewing someone I actually felt bad for and therefore didn\'t want to take an ironic stance against him. It actually turned out to be a really funny piece.', 'Rob Corddry', 'funny'),
(4907, 'I don\'t think my judgment is that good. I don\'t know what is funny.', 'Jerry Stiller', 'funny'),
(4908, 'It\'s funny the hardest thing to do is to make something look like it\'s fast loose and improvised and get somebody to laugh.', 'Abel Ferrara', 'funny'),
(4909, 'Sometimes we have to actually say I think you\'re really funny but none of your jokes are going to make it on the air. So just answer my questions. Seriously.', 'Rob Corddry', 'funny'),
