(7092, 'I always thought the biggest failing of Americans was their lack of irony. They are very serious there! Naturally there are exceptions... the Jewish Italian and Irish humor of the East Coast.', 'Colin Firth', 'humor'),
(7093, 'Have a sense of humor about life - you will need it. And be courteous.', 'Peter Jennings', 'humor'),
(7094, 'If I didn\'t try to eavesdrop on every bus ride I take or look for the humor when I go for a walk I would just be depressed all the time.', 'Lynda Barry', 'humor'),
(7095, 'Poor David Hume is dying fast but with more real cheerfulness and good humor and with more real resignation to the necessary course of things than any whining Christian ever dyed with pretended resignation to the will of God.', 'Adam Smith', 'humor'),
(7096, 'The nation that complacently and fearfully allows its artists and writers to become suspected rather than respected is no longer regarded as a nation possessed with humor or depth.', 'James Thurber', 'humor'),
(7097, 'I\'ve got a great sense of humor.', 'Anthony Hopkins', 'humor'),
(7098, 'We can\'t understand when we\'re pregnant or when our siblings are expecting how profound it is to have a shared history with a younger generation: blood genes humor. It means we were actually here on Earth for a time - like the Egyptians with their pyramid', 'Anne Lamott', 'humor'),
(7099, 'People of humor are always in some degree people of genius.', 'Samuel Taylor Coleridge', 'humor'),
(7100, 'It\'s easier to sit there and say you don\'t like feminists because they don\'t have a sense of humor.', 'Joan Jett', 'humor'),
(7101, 'I\'ve met a lot of people who\'ve lost their jobs and they still have a sense of humor.', 'Louis C. K.', 'humor'),
(7102, 'I don\'t understand how somebody wouldn\'t have a sense of humor about themselves.', 'John Malkovich', 'humor'),
(7103, 'There is also this benefit in brag that the speaker is unconsciously expressing his own ideal. Humor him by all means draw it all out and hold him to it.', 'Miguel de Cervantes', 'humor'),
(7104, 'A little perspective like a little humor goes a long way.', 'Allen Klein', 'humor'),
(7105, 'There are certain things I learned when I first started learning about acting to try and place the character physically and emotionally. And the way you place them emotionally is often with humor.', 'David Duchovny', 'humor'),
(7106, 'A lot of people into Tool for some reason are not interested in humor.', 'Maynard James Keenan', 'humor'),
(7107, 'I\'m just very amused by five-year-old humor.', 'Kesha', 'humor'),
(7108, 'If the blood humor is too strong and robust calm it with balance and harmony.', 'Xun Zi', 'humor'),
(7109, 'What we\'re doing is fun - if you have any sense of humor at all!', 'Calvin Klein', 'humor'),
(7110, 'As far as humor goes I\'ve always been a very insecure person and I\'ve always wanted to be liked.', 'Peter Steele', 'humor'),
(7111, 'It\'s good to be able to laugh at yourself and the problems you face in life. Sense of humor can save you.', 'Margaret Cho', 'humor'),
(7112, 'Married people should not be quick to hear what is said by either when in ill humor.', 'Samuel Richardson', 'humor'),
(7113, 'From sixteen to twenty all women kept in humor by their hopes and by their attractions appear to be good-natured.', 'Samuel Richardson', 'humor'),
(7114, 'My father could be very witty even if the humor was always on the darker side of irony.', 'Maurice Sendak', 'humor'),
(7115, 'I suppose I miss the British cynicism and the humor.', 'Rod Stewart', 'humor'),
(7116, 'People who know me  they know I have a sense of humor I\'m a bit of a joker a bit of a clown really and I would love someone to exploit that side of me and send me a romantic comedy.', 'Gary Oldman', 'humor'),
(7117, 'Congratulations you have a sense of humor. And to those who didn\'t: Go stick your head in the mud.', 'Jesse Ventura', 'humor'),
(7118, 'It\'s your outlook on life that counts. If you take yourself lightly and don\'t take yourself too seriously pretty soon you can find the humor in our everyday lives. And sometimes it can be a lifesaver.', 'Betty White', 'humor'),
(7119, 'The total absence of humor from the Bible is one of the most singular things in all literature.', 'Alfred North Whitehead', 'humor'),
(7120, 'If this humor be the safety of our race then it is due largely to the infusion into the American people of the Irish brain.', 'William Howard Taft', 'humor'),
(7121, 'You find out in life that people really like you funny. So what do you give \'em? Humor. And then if you show them the other side they don\'t like you as much. I find too that I can hide behind the idiot\'s mask being funny and you never see the sorrow or th', 'Terry Bradshaw', 'humor'),
(7122, 'It has always surprised me how little attention philosophers have paid to humor since it is a more significant process of mind than reason. Reason can only sort out perceptions but the humor process is involved in changing them.', 'Edward de Bono', 'humor'),
(7123, 'Feature-length film comedy is harder to pull off than the episodic sitcom - it doesn\'t have the same factory machinery up and running teams of writers putting familiar characters through permutations - but that doesn\'t explain the widening quality gap tha', 'James Wolcott', 'humor'),
(7124, 'When you say a friend has a sense of humor do you mean that he makes you laugh or that he can make you laugh?', 'Max Frisch', 'humor'),
(7125, 'Humor is very very risky particularly for a candidate unless he\'s been in so long that it just doesn\'t matter and he\'s not running for president. But it\'s just that people are so sensitive and so touchy and you\'re just going to upset somebody without ever', 'Mark Russell', 'humor'),
(7126, 'The reason why you know more funny dudes than funny chicks is that dudes are funnier than chicks. If my daughter has a mediocre sense of humor I\'m just gonna tell her \'Be a staff writer for a sitcom. Because they\'ll have to hire you they can\'t really fire', 'Adam Carolla', 'humor'),
(7127, 'You may not be able to change a situation but with humor you can change your attitude about it.', 'Allen Klein', 'humor'),
(7128, 'My life is part humor part roses part thorns.', 'Bret Michaels', 'humor'),
(7129, 'Newspaper people once celebrated as founts of ribald humor and uncouth fun have of late lost all their gaiety and small wonder.', 'Russell Baker', 'humor'),
(7130, 'I like to deal with EVERY aspect of our condition and that means terror and humor in equal mix. Some books have more room for humor than others.', 'Dean Koontz', 'humor'),
(7131, 'Our records if you have a dark sense of humor were funny but our records weren\'t about comedy. They were about protests fantasy confrontation and all that.', 'Ice Cube', 'humor'),
(7132, 'I think God gave us senses of humor and we should use them.', 'Vera Farmiga', 'humor'),
(7133, 'A lot of stars don\'t have a sense of humor.', 'Kathy Griffin', 'humor'),
(7134, 'You\'ve got to have a sense of humor to keep your sanity.', 'Lance Bass', 'humor'),
(7135, 'Writing a novel is one of those modern rites of passage I think that lead us from an innocent world of contentment drunkenness and good humor to a state of chronic edginess and the perpetual scanning of bank statements.', 'J. G. Ballard', 'humor'),
(7136, 'I could not tread these perilous paths in safety if I did not keep a saving sense of humor.', 'Horatio Nelson', 'humor'),
(7137, 'Well darkness with humor... I\'m not an extremely suicidal or sad person.', 'Peter Steele', 'humor'),
(7138, 'I have this horrible sense of humor where I think discomfort is funny - partly because I experience discomfort a lot and it\'s a way of laughing at it and getting a release.', 'Joaquin Phoenix', 'humor'),
(7139, 'Well I mean if a joke or humor is bawdy it\'s got to be funny enough to warrant it. You can\'t just have it bawdy or dirty just for the sake of being that - it\'s got to be funny.', 'Betty White', 'humor'),
(7140, 'I like bawdy humor. I love bawdy humor but not dirty humor.', 'Betty White', 'humor'),
(7141, 'It is characteristic of all deep human problems that they are not to be approached without some humor and some bewilderment.', 'Freeman Dyson', 'humor'),
(7142, 'I love the diversity of America. I love the plain normal sense of humor Americans have. It is not wicked like in some countries. And I also love how new America is.', 'Antonio Banderas', 'humor'),
(7143, 'If one tends to be a humorous person and you have a sense of humor the rest of your life then you can certainly lighten the load I think by bringing that to your trials and tribulations. It\'s easy to have a sense of humor when everything is going well.', 'Alan Thicke', 'humor'),
(7144, 'Humor is such a wonderful thing helping you realize what a fool you are but how beautiful that is at the same time.', 'Lynda Barry', 'humor'),
(7145, 'Every time I do a movie like \'Finding Neverland\' or \'Chocolat\' or \'Shakespeare\' in Love\' we deal with the creative process but there\'s humor and fun along the way. I always love that kind of movie.', 'Harvey Weinstein', 'humor'),
(7146, 'There is nothing like the way people feel after they\'ve seen \'The Intouchables.\' They feel amazing. The word of mouth on this film is incredible. It\'s intelligent-feeling good. You\'re not insulted by the low-browness or stupidity of some of the humor. It\'', 'Harvey Weinstein', 'humor'),
(7147, 'There are just certain things that turn my head. It may be a girl\'s sense of humor it may be her wit or her belief system it could be a lot of different things.', 'Jensen Ackles', 'humor'),
(7148, 'I find that people find a way out of misery through humor and it\'s humor that\'s often unacceptable to people who are not in quite such a state of misery.', 'Danny Boyle', 'humor'),
(7149, 'I\'m lucky that my real-life Mom has both a great sense of humor about herself and an amazing ability to slip into complete denial if the subject matter gets a little too close to home.', 'Cathy Guisewite', 'humor'),
(7150, 'When humor can be made to alternate with melancholy one has a success but when the same things are funny and melancholic at the same time it\'s just wonderful.', 'Francois Truffaut', 'humor'),
(7151, 'I want someone who can keep me on my toes has a good sense of humor and a good heart.', 'Carmen Electra', 'humor'),
(7152, 'I have a very silly sense of humor. I\'ve never laughed harder in my entire life than seeing someone with toilet paper stuck on the bottom of their shoe.', 'Paula Poundstone', 'humor'),
(7153, 'Whether it\'s viewers of the show or readers of my columns and books I\'m consistently impressed with their wit humor and insight. That goes for about 95 percent of the audience. The other five percent are why the \'Delete\' option and restraining orders were', 'Richard Roeper', 'humor'),
(7154, 'Mixing humor and politics is something that works.', 'Bryan Cranston', 'humor'),
(7155, 'People with no humor they\'re outta my life.', 'Patti LaBelle', 'humor'),
(7156, 'My fam is just a regular family. But all of them have great senses of humor.', 'Dane Cook', 'humor'),
(7157, 'The rejection that we all take and the sadness and the aggravation and the loss of jobs and all of the things that we live through in our lives without a sense of humor I don\'t know how people make it.', 'Marlo Thomas', 'humor'),
(7158, 'I don\'t have a caustic sense of humor. What I find funny that humor comes from a much gentler place.', 'Vera Farmiga', 'humor'),
(7159, 'I love poking fun at myself. I have a rather mean sense of humor.', 'Alton Brown', 'humor'),
(7160, 'I think a lot of humor is about distracting yourself. Pretend you\'re not trying to make it funny. Because for some reason the effort to be funny smells like sulphur in our culture.', 'Sloane Crosley', 'humor'),
(7161, 'It\'s funny. People often compare me to other humor essayists. They\'re usually quite nice comparisons I will accept those gladly. But I am always sort of appalled at the idea of being lumped with other more chick-y female writers. And the truth is probably', 'Sloane Crosley', 'humor'),
(7162, 'I think that sense of humor is important in marriage. A sense of humor gets people through marriage.', 'Kyle Chandler', 'humor'),
(7163, 'Sometimes a scene may be about one thing and it may end up still being about that but the emotionality of it comes from somewhere else or the humor of it comes from somewhere else and it gives it that real-life quality.', 'Kyle Chandler', 'humor'),
(7164, 'The darker the film the more vital everyone\'s sense of humor is on set.', 'Eric Bana', 'humor'),
(7165, 'You know I\'m Australian and we have got the worst sense of humor. We are cruel to each other.', 'Steve Irwin', 'humor'),
(7166, 'I have wit in my work and a sense of humor but I do not use irony in any way.', 'John Zorn', 'humor'),
(7167, 'I find intelligence sexy. I find a sense of humor sexy. I find sensitivity sexy.', 'Nicole Appleton', 'humor'),
(7168, 'If I ever have sex with someone I might be able to develop a sense of humor.', 'Kate Beckinsale', 'humor'),
(7169, 'I realized women and humor were linked very closely.', 'Craig Ferguson', 'humor'),
(7170, 'Me and Matt love to argue but in general our sense of humor is pretty much alike.', 'Trey Parker', 'humor'),
(7171, 'We are in the comics the last frontier of good wholesome family humor and entertainment.', 'Bil Keane', 'humor'),
(7172, 'I just am a snob when it comes to humor.', 'Courteney Cox', 'humor'),
(7173, 'One of my favorite things about \'Star Trek\' wasn\'t just the overt banter but the humor in that show about the relationships between the main characters and their reactions to the situations they would face there was a lot of comedy in that show without ev', 'J. J. Abrams', 'humor'),
(7174, 'God has a most wicked sense of humor.', 'Maureen O\'Hara', 'humor'),
(7175, 'There are two insults no human being will endure: that he has no sense of humor and that he has never known trouble.', 'Sinclair Lewis', 'humor'),
(7176, 'I wore goofy hats to school and did musical theater. Most people thought I was a dork. But if you have a sense of humor about it no one can bring you down.', 'Zac Efron', 'humor'),
(7177, 'Tony and I had a good on and off screen relationship we are two very different people but we did share a sense of humor we now live in different parts of the world but when we find ourselves in the same place it is more or less as if there had been no yea', 'Roger Moore', 'humor'),
(7178, 'Cathy was the first widely syndicated humor strip created by a woman. The strip was pretty revolutionary at the time not only because it starred a female but also because it was so emotionally honest about all the conflicting feelings many women had in 19', 'Cathy Guisewite', 'humor'),
(7179, 'There\'s always a source for humor.', 'Calvin Trillin', 'humor'),
(7180, 'If you\'re that hypersensitive about color and don\'t have a sense of humor don\'t marry out of your race.', 'Laura Schlessinger', 'humor'),
(7181, 'The humor section is the last place an author wants to be. They put your stuff next to collections of Cathy cartoons.', 'David Sedaris', 'humor'),
