(7348, 'We\'re starting to push the envelope in terms of the expectations and you can also have your own style personality and sense of humor because now we\'re allowed to.', 'Lisa Guerrero', 'humor'),
(7349, 'If I can\'t see the humor in it how am I going to be funny?', 'Casey Affleck', 'humor'),
(7350, 'It\'s very hard to write humor.', 'Mark Strand', 'humor'),
(7351, 'Humor has become so cliche and boring that nothing\'s funny anymore unless it involves something totally disgusting that offends somebody or makes them feel really uncomfortable.', 'Tom DeLonge', 'humor'),
(7352, 'I don\'t need someone with a hot body. He can be fat or overweight and have a belly. It\'s very much about style and substance and humor interest curiosity and really being smart.', 'Kate Walsh', 'humor'),
(7353, 'Bands from Akron have a sense of humor and don\'t tend to take themselves too seriously.', 'Dan Auerbach', 'humor'),
(7354, 'Suspense is very important. Even though this is humor and they\'re short stories that theory of building suspense is still there.', 'Sergio Aragones', 'humor'),
(7355, 'I\'ve always chosen my band members based on their sense of humor. It might sound stupid but it means not only are they fun to live with on a tour bus for years but humor implies intelligence.', 'Kristin Hersh', 'humor'),
(7356, 'I am a great believer that what makes our show different is the humor.', 'Treat Williams', 'humor'),
(7357, 'Humor that is edgy is never squeaky clean.', 'Jeff Ross', 'humor'),
(7358, 'Athletes tend to have less of a sense of humor than most people. They are heroes to so many. That might be part of it.', 'Jeff Ross', 'humor'),
(7359, 'I always felt different as a kid and the Kinks were like \'Yeah we\'re the Kinks.\' Celebrate your difference don\'t be afraid of your sense of humor or your personality or who you are. It emboldened me.', 'Michael Weatherly', 'humor'),
(7360, 'There are psychological repercussions to illness and we need a little more help to get through the effects not only on the afflicted but on the family. And I think there\'s even a place for humor in that.', 'Alan Thicke', 'humor'),
(7361, 'I don\'t really dissect comedy. Nothing kills off humor more than overanalyzing it.', 'David Steinberg', 'humor'),
(7362, 'Humor has always been important to me. If there is a shield of faith that you can keep up against difficulties humor is the Teflon coating.', 'Laurel Lee', 'humor'),
(7363, 'He has such a patronizing tone and manner and such a sarcastic sense of humor. I found him rather brutal a kind of elegant brutality which appealed. No I think he came pretty much off the page.', 'Jeremy Northam', 'humor'),
(7364, 'I think I\'m too cynical for L.A. My sense of humor doesn\'t go down well here which probably affects my love life. I need to have a laugh track following me around so people know I\'m trying to be funny.', 'Teddy Thompson', 'humor'),
(7365, 'Back in 2004 Kellie Overbey handed me her play \'Girl Talk\' to read. I fell in love with her brutally delicious humor and the fearlessly deft way in which she drew her characters. They jumped off the page and begged me to give them a space in which to stom', 'Carrie Preston', 'humor'),
(7366, 'Robert Walker as Bruno was excellent. He had elegance and humor and the proper fondness for his mother.', 'Patricia Highsmith', 'humor'),
(7367, 'You can\'t do anything to be funny. That\'s cringeworthy. If your humor comes out of a place of love every time you don\'t make the joke bigger than you. The funniest comedians are in touch with their emotional level.', 'John Krasinski', 'humor'),
(7368, 'I think it would be hard to go the distance in this business without a sense of humor.', 'Patricia Clarkson', 'humor'),
(7369, 'G.I. humor is similar to cop humor.', 'Nelson DeMille', 'humor'),
(7370, 'Humor is healing.', 'Brad Garrett', 'humor'),
(7371, 'There was a time I was very much blaming the way I felt on L.A that it was a vacuum of creativity of humor or anything organic and I was really angry at the place. But then today I feel completely different - I love L.A.!', 'Naomi Watts', 'humor'),
(7372, 'All I try to do is as earnestly and as acutely as I can conceive a character and try to portray this character just honestly. If the humor is within the absurdity and the awfulness of situations then let it be seen that way.', 'Patrick Warburton', 'humor'),
(7373, 'But if you read Jane Austen you know that she had a wicked sense of humor. Not only was she funny but her early writing was very dark and had a gothic tone to it.', 'Seth Grahame-Smith', 'humor'),
(7374, 'I think it\'s because it\'s so different and it takes risks. Plus it\'s really smart humor. It gives the audience credit in terms of not needing to tell them when to laugh. I love that about the show. There\'s no laugh track.', 'Sarah Chalke', 'humor'),
(7375, 'Humor is the ability to see three sides to one coin.', 'Ned Rorem', 'humor'),
(7376, 'The script was just the best I\'d read in a long time and I love the humor which I wasn\'t expecting and I like the fact that my six year old daughter can see the show without being you know protected from it.', 'Stephen Collins', 'humor'),
(7377, 'I really wouldn\'t want to live in America. I found New York claustrophobic and dirty. I missed England when I was there simple things like smells and the British sense of humor.', 'Jonny Lee Miller', 'humor'),
(7378, 'I think Damien Hirst is hilarious. And I think he\'s a true artist. He\'s not hilarious first I think he is a real artist and I also think he\'s got an amazing sense of humor.', 'Jemima Kirke', 'humor'),
(7379, 'I think great humor lies in playing the truth of a situation.', 'Brendan Coyle', 'humor');
