(7395, 'People may think of Southern humor in terms of missing teeth and outhouse accidents but the best of it is a rich vein running through the best of Southern literature.', 'Roy Blount Jr.', 'humor'),
(7396, 'Sense of humor is important in life not just in clothing. How boring to live a life in beige.', 'Jean Pigozzi', 'humor'),
