(7412, 'Those who knew Lincoln described him as an extraordinarily funny man. Humor was an essential aspect of his temperament. He laughed he explained so he did not weep.', 'Doris Kearns Goodwin', 'humor'),
(7413, 'I think that some books are more successful than others to certain readers. People who read my books for the humor they\'re going to love one book. People who read my books for the mystery they might not like that book quite as much.', 'Janet Evanovich', 'humor'),
(7414, 'You can get through very serious and sometimes horrible and sometimes embarrassing and very awkward situations with humor. It gives us a way out.', 'Janet Evanovich', 'humor'),
(7415, 'We don\'t appreciate the value of humor sometimes.', 'Janet Evanovich', 'humor'),
(7416, 'I\'ve learned to have a sense of humor about myself. Lord knows everyone else does!', 'Debbie Gibson', 'humor'),
(7417, 'M*A*S*H offered real characters and everybody identified with them because they had such soul. The humor was intelligent and it always assumed that you had an intellect.', 'Loretta Swit', 'humor'),
(7418, 'We have always had gross humor. But we try for funny not gross.', 'Shawn Wayans', 'humor'),
(7419, 'The quickest way to defuse fear or insecurity or anger is usually humor. I think comics figure that out quickly and once you figure it out you think \'Hey if I can do this and get paid that would be kind of cool.\'', 'Billy Gardell', 'humor'),
(7420, 'I often have said that to be a college president you need a thick skin a good sense of humor and nerves like sewer pipes.', 'Gordon Gee', 'humor'),
(7421, 'Humor is imperative more important than food. You have a choice when someone dies. You can lie down or get back into life. Do something for someone else.', 'Doris Roberts', 'humor'),
(7422, 'We have a certain warped sense of humor in Scandinavia and that is what comes across in the choices in a lot of our movies.', 'Connie Nielsen', 'humor'),
(7423, 'When a chick has a sense of humor there\'s nothing more attractive.', 'Dylan O\'Brien', 'humor'),
(7424, 'The President has a wonderful sense of humor which is one of the reasons it is so much fun to work for him.', 'Karen Hughes', 'humor'),
(7425, 'I don\'t have a very quick sense of humor.', 'Florenz Ziegfeld', 'humor'),
(7426, 'If a dog doesn\'t put you first where are you both? In what relation? A dog needs God. It lives by your glances your wishes. It even shares your humor. This happens about the fifth year. If it doesn\'t happen you are only keeping an animal.', 'Enid Bagnold', 'humor'),
(7427, 'It\'s great to be able to connect parents with children both emotionally and through humor. I look forward to exploring family entertainment once again and examining the specifics of our day-to-day lives against the backdrop of an extraordinary adventure.', 'Jon Favreau', 'humor'),
