(7453, 'Next to power without honor the most dangerous thing in the world is power without humor.', 'Eric Sevareid', 'humor'),
(7454, 'A boy is naturally full of humor.', 'Robert Powell', 'humor'),
(7455, 'Prior to Wordsworth humor was an essential part of poetry. I mean they don\'t call them Shakespeare comedies for nothing.', 'William Collins', 'humor'),
(7456, 'I think humor is a very serious thing. I use it as a way of weakening the reader\'s defenses so that I can more easily take him to something more.', 'William Collins', 'humor'),
