(7600, 'If you would take you must first give this is the beginning of intelligence.', 'Lao Tzu', 'intelligence'),
(7601, 'The first method for estimating the intelligence of a ruler is to look at the men he has around him.', 'Niccolo Machiavelli', 'intelligence'),
(7602, 'Bottom line is I didn\'t return to Apple to make a fortune. I\'ve been very lucky in my life and already have one. When I was 25 my net worth was $100 million or so. I decided then that I wasn\'t going to let it ruin my life. There\'s no way you could ever sp', 'Steve Jobs', 'intelligence'),
(7603, 'Everything in the universe has a purpose. Indeed the invisible intelligence that flows through everything in a purposeful fashion is also flowing through you.', 'Wayne Dyer', 'intelligence'),
(7604, 'Shall I not have intelligence with the earth? Am I not partly leaves and vegetable mould myself.', 'Henry David Thoreau', 'intelligence'),
(7605, 'I would like to take you seriously but to do so would be an affront to your intelligence.', 'George Bernard Shaw', 'intelligence'),
(7606, 'The modern mind is in complete disarray. Knowledge has stretched itself to the point where neither the world nor our intelligence can find any foot-hold. It is a fact that we are suffering from nihilism.', 'Albert Camus', 'intelligence'),
