(7623, 'We will strengthen our security by building missile defense restoring our military might and standing by and strengthening our intelligence officers.', 'Mitt Romney', 'intelligence'),
(7624, 'I\'ve always felt that a person\'s intelligence is directly reflected by the number of conflicting points of view he can entertain simultaneously on the same topic.', 'Abigail Adams', 'intelligence'),
(7625, 'Neither a lofty degree of intelligence nor imagination nor both together go to the making of genius. Love love love that is the soul of genius.', 'Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart', 'intelligence'),
(7626, 'In our civilization and under our republican form of government intelligence is so highly honored that it is rewarded by exemption from the cares of office.', 'Ambrose Bierce', 'intelligence'),
