(7658, 'To educate the intelligence is to expand the horizon of its wants and desires.', 'James Russell Lowell', 'intelligence'),
(7659, 'The intelligence of the creature known as a crowd is the square root of the number of people in it.', 'Terry Pratchett', 'intelligence'),
(7660, 'Intelligence is quickness in seeing things as they are.', 'George Santayana', 'intelligence'),
(7661, 'There can be no two opinions as to what a highbrow is. He is the man or woman of thoroughbred intelligence who rides his mind at a gallop across country in pursuit of an idea.', 'Virginia Woolf', 'intelligence'),
