(8509, 'He will therefore have to use what knowledge he can achieve not to shape the results as the craftsman shapes his handiwork but rather to cultivate a growth by providing the appropriate environment in the manner in which the gardener does this for his plan', 'Friedrich August von Hayek', 'knowledge'),
(8510, 'What is called an acute knowledge of human nature is mostly nothing but the observer\'s own weaknesses reflected back from others.', 'Georg C. Lichtenberg', 'knowledge'),
