(11092, 'I don\'t write poems and put them to music. Just let things flow.', 'Martin Gore', 'music'),
(11093, 'I scientifically engineer my music to be as accessible as possible.', 'John Mayer', 'music'),
(11094, 'It\'s almost charity work what people have done turning other people on to my music.', 'John Mayer', 'music'),
(11095, 'I just change with the times. I really don\'t have a say in what\'s going on. Music was here before me.', 'Snoop Dogg', 'music'),
(11096, 'Very much like that and very much a loner do you know and I didn\'t fit really into sport or all kind of group activities as a kid I couldn\'t find a niche. And music was not really part of the kind of village curriculum it would you know.', 'Eric Clapton', 'music'),
(11097, 'Although they can do it all the time you know they\'re far better than me on a musically on a theoretical music level. You know they\'re out of my league.', 'Eric Clapton', 'music'),
(11098, 'Music became a healer for me.', 'Eric Clapton', 'music'),
(11099, 'When all the original blues guys are gone you start to realize that someone has to tend to the tradition. I recognize that I have some responsibility to keep the music alive and it\'s a pretty honorable position to be in.', 'Eric Clapton', 'music'),
(11100, 'But I did go to music really early on even when I was 4 or 5 I was responding to music probably in ways other kids were not.', 'Eric Clapton', 'music'),
(11101, 'The way I feel about music is that there is no right and wrong. Only true and false.', 'Fiona Apple', 'music'),
(11102, 'I always knew I\'d be in music in some sort of capacity. I didn\'t know if I\'d be successful at it but I knew I\'d be doing something in it. Maybe get a job in a record store. Maybe even play in a band. I never got into this to be a star.', 'Bryan Adams', 'music'),
(11103, 'I like to make music I like rap music. Even if I\'m white I support that music. If I want to support it or any other white kid wants to support it more power to them.', 'Kid Rock', 'music'),
(11104, 'That\'s what I love from metal and that\'s what I love from hip-hop. That\'s what I love from any music that\'s hard that\'s got an edge to it-The attitude in it.', 'Kid Rock', 'music'),
(11105, 'I\'ve never believed that pop music is escapist trash. There\'s always a darkness in it even amidst great pop music.', 'Thom Yorke', 'music'),
(11106, 'I always believed in the music we did and that\'s why it was uncompromising.', 'Jimmy Page', 'music'),
(11107, 'I love 70\'s music.', 'Laura Linney', 'music'),
(11108, 'Music is what our feelings sound like.', 'Vera Farmiga', 'music'),
(11109, 'Also because people like to multitask in a way if you\'ve got a bit of music on in the background and the lyrical content is making you want to listen to it then that would probably put you off the texting you wanted to do. I think people like things that ', 'Jarvis Cocker', 'music'),
(11110, 'Music is a language and different people who come along are each using that language to do something different but all coming at it in a similar vein inasmuch as it\'s always community based and for the most part nonprofit. Most bands don\'t ever come withi', 'Ian MacKaye', 'music'),
(11111, 'Put you energy into music. If it fails you you can become an accountant or a dentist. And then if you become a dentist or an accountant it\'s too late to become a musician afterwards.', 'Peter Tork', 'music'),
(11112, 'We forget that this music music made by my brothers and sisters is still a baby. It\'s just beginning. When I think of the possibilities it makes me smile.', 'Barry White', 'music'),
(11113, 'You can never stop discovering music.', 'Rashida Jones', 'music'),
(11114, 'What\'s missing from pop music is danger.', 'Prince', 'music'),
(11115, 'Music is hugely important to me.', 'Rashida Jones', 'music'),
(11116, 'You listen to a piece of music and it will remind you of something - it might make you happy it might make you sad but it is very emotive. And I think that Duran Duran have always understood that.', 'Nick Rhodes', 'music'),
(11117, 'Music breaks my heart constantly.', 'Rashida Jones', 'music'),
(11118, 'Comedy is like music and the way to make the best music is to have skilled musicians in your band.', 'Rashida Jones', 'music'),
(11119, 'I don\'t want to be an artist go on tour and make a video and wear sexy clothes. I would just love to make music.', 'Rashida Jones', 'music'),
(11120, 'I have one piece of music since 1997 and I don\'t see it having lyrics. Where does it go in this world? So I haven\'t recorded it.', 'Joni Mitchell', 'music'),
(11121, 'There was this mountain village in Russia where my music was getting in on some German radio station. I remember this because music used to get up to Saskatchewan from Texas. Late at night after the local station closed down.', 'Joni Mitchell', 'music'),
(11122, 'In some ways my gift for music and writing was born out of tragedy really and loss.', 'Joni Mitchell', 'music'),
(11123, 'I see music as fluid architecture.', 'Joni Mitchell', 'music'),
(11124, 'To enjoy my music you need depth and emotionality.', 'Joni Mitchell', 'music'),
(11125, 'The considerations of a corporation especially now have nothing to do with art or music.', 'Joni Mitchell', 'music'),
(11126, 'I came through folk music simply because it was easy to get into it.', 'Joni Mitchell', 'music'),
(11127, 'I heard someone from the music business saying they are no longer looking for talent they want people with a certain look and a willingness to cooperate.', 'Joni Mitchell', 'music'),
(11128, 'Writing has laws of perspective of light and shade just as painting does or music. If you are born knowing them fine. If not learn them. Then rearrange the rules to suit yourself.', 'Truman Capote', 'music'),
(11129, 'Music will always be my No. 1 passion but I don\'t have to be doing it professionally. It\'s not really about that for me anymore. I feel like I don\'t have to look at it as a career. I can just rest in it and just be.', 'Jessica Simpson', 'music'),
(11130, 'When you grow up in the music industry trying to be Britney Spears because that\'s what sells records and then you realize \'All I have to do is be myself? I should have thought of that a long time ago\' it feels good to have success come from what\'s actuall', 'Jessica Simpson', 'music'),
(11131, 'All art constantly aspires towards the condition of music.', 'Walter Pater', 'music'),
(11132, 'I write music with an exclamation point!', 'Richard Wagner', 'music'),
(11133, 'What is music anyway? It\'s a form of communication and that\'s why I play the kind of music that I think - that I hope - can communicate with people.', 'Kenny G', 'music'),
(11134, 'I was a good amateur but only an average professional. I soon realized that there was a limit to how far I could rise in the music business so I left the band and enrolled at New York University.', 'Alan Greenspan', 'music'),
(11135, 'Drums just always sounded like the most fun part of that good music for me.', 'Levon Helm', 'music'),
(11136, 'For some reason the evolutionists have not come up with an evolution-based explanation for why human beings react so powerfully to music. But surely they will.', 'Dennis Prager', 'music'),
(11137, 'I\'d love to do a modern-day musical that\'s full of original music. To get your contemporaries to sing and dance without looking foolish and for it to be transformational and magical and all those things a musical is supposed to be.', 'Danny Boyle', 'music'),
(11138, 'In these confused times the role of classical music is at the very core of the struggle to reassert cultural and ethical values that have always characterized our country and for which we have traditionally been honored and respected outside our shores.', 'Lorin Maazel', 'music'),
(11139, 'I tend to score with songs from Western pop music.', 'Danny Boyle', 'music'),
(11140, 'Distance doesn\'t exist in fact and neither does time. Vibrations from love or music can be felt everywhere at all times.', 'Yoko Ono', 'music'),
(11141, 'Ain\'t nobody making music to not be heard and the easiest way to be heard is to be on the radio but you should never compromise who you are your values or your morals.', 'Talib Kweli', 'music'),
(11142, 'You can have great sequences with music but if you don\'t have the acting you\'re bored after 15 minutes. Or not bored but you\'re like \'So what?\'', 'Danny Boyle', 'music'),
(11143, 'We talk a lot on \'Biggest Loser\' about how fitness is a natural antidepressant how it burns off stress. What I like about running is that it gives me time alone. I\'m always busy with people at work with my kids. I love getting out for a run by myself and ', 'Alison Sweeney', 'music'),
(11144, 'I\'m not trying to keep up or adapt. I\'m allowing myself to grow evolve and create new music.', 'LL Cool J', 'music'),
(11145, 'I love that sense of change that you\'d get in pop music every three minutes every four minutes.', 'Danny Boyle', 'music'),
(11146, 'I want to promote poetry to the point where you got all the baldhead kids running around doing poetry getting the music out of the way and having only words the spoken word and then see what happens.', 'Russell Simmons', 'music'),
(11147, 'Hip-hop\'s always reached out to kids. If you look at the last 10 big albums it might seem ironic. But when I look at the history of this music it\'s always had a lot of positivity.', 'LL Cool J', 'music'),
(11148, 'I sing a mixture of everything from opera folk music Broadway. It\'s a mix of things.', 'Katherine Jenkins', 'music'),
(11149, 'I\'m really an inner spirit that only makes itself known through the music. A lot of people think I\'m an introvert or quiet and moody. I\'ve even heard some people say that there\'s a certain mystery or darkness about me. I\'m not that way. I\'m just really in', 'Faith Evans', 'music'),
(11150, 'Nobody was listening when I learned how to play music. But there\'s something about being on stage talking to the audience looking at them and smiling that\'s always been difficult for me. I\'m a lot more comfortable now but there are still moments of awkwar', 'Norah Jones', 'music'),
(11151, 'My music appeals in America. There is less of the purist criticism I get here. And to be a hit in the U.S... what singer doesn\'t have that dream?', 'Katherine Jenkins', 'music'),
(11152, 'The one thing that kept our family together was the music. The only thing that our family would share emotionally was to have our dad cry over something the kids did with music.', 'Dennis Wilson', 'music'),
(11153, 'What I was going for in the first two albums I didn\'t necessarily achieve. Because I was young and because it was my first time out. And the second album was such a \'quickie\' sort of \'Let\'s just get it over with!\' But the kind of music I make there\'s a lo', 'Norah Jones', 'music'),
(11154, 'Oh stuff the critics. I don\'t care. Too many people are snooty about classical. Look I wasn\'t brought up in a home where we listened to classical music. It was a singing teacher that thought it would be best for my voice. Then I moved into crossover. And ', 'Katherine Jenkins', 'music'),
(11155, 'When I moved to New York I fell head over heels back into country music and probably \'cause I missed something about Texas.', 'Norah Jones', 'music'),
(11156, 'I love to listen to pop music and I admire people who do that but I don\'t think I would ever be a very good pop star. I always leave that singing voice for the shower! I wouldn\'t put it out in the world!', 'Katherine Jenkins', 'music'),
(11157, 'I wasn\'t very aware of pop music because I attended an arts school. For me it was all about jazz.', 'Norah Jones', 'music'),
(11158, 'I think maybe because of the kind of music I sing people want to believe you\'re a diva. They can\'t believe after eight years and eight albums you\'re still relatively sane. I feel like they almost want me to throw something at somebody.', 'Katherine Jenkins', 'music'),
(11159, 'A lot of my music is slow and subtle. The subtly is what I enjoy about making music.', 'Norah Jones', 'music'),
(11160, 'You\'re now getting a new breed of people like Il Divo and Andrea Bocelli and I think that\'s why people feel less intimidated by classical music than they once did.', 'Katherine Jenkins', 'music'),
(11161, 'My first two records are so simply constructed. The reason isn\'t because I wanted to make simple music. It\'s because I don\'t really have the chops.', 'Norah Jones', 'music'),
(11162, 'I love recording music.', 'J. J. Abrams', 'music'),
(11163, 'It\'s true there\'s a lot of melancholy in my music. I don\'t know why I\'m not a melancholy person. I\'ve always been drawn to it. Ever since I was a kid if I had an album I would play the ballads on repeat.', 'Norah Jones', 'music'),
(11164, 'For me making music is part social part interaction part collaboration.', 'Norah Jones', 'music'),
(11165, 'I was in choir in school. I kind of just did it. I already knew I wanted to sing. My music program in my school wasn\'t really great - people didn\'t really want to be part of the choir they didn\'t want to do the plays and stuff like that. It definitely was', 'Lea Michele', 'music'),
(11166, 'Disco is music for dancing and people will always want to dance.', 'Giorgio Moroder', 'music'),
(11167, 'I\'ve been told the weirdest things: \'Yeah I love taking a bath to your music!\' or \'I gave birth to my daughter while listening to your music.\'', 'Norah Jones', 'music'),
(11168, 'We\'re real people and we\'re a band that\'s been playing on the scene for a long time. We\'ve made a lot of friends and one enemy we\'ve always had was the NME. They\'ve always basically slated us and they\'ve basically never ever written about the music.', 'Dan Hawkins', 'music'),
(11169, 'Success and the art of making music are two different things for me.', 'Norah Jones', 'music'),
(11170, 'I just want to keep making music recording and trying different things. I don\'t want to do the same thing all the time.', 'Norah Jones', 'music'),
(11171, 'I\'m always going to do that - record and make music.', 'Norah Jones', 'music'),
(11172, 'I love slow music.', 'Norah Jones', 'music'),
(11173, 'I genuinely don\'t feel that anything that\'s been written or said about me has overshadowed my music and that\'s the most important thing as far as I\'m concerned.', 'Norah Jones', 'music'),
(11174, 'I didn\'t think it was fair to my music to label me as the daughter of somebody - I didn\'t think it described me very well and I didn\'t think it had anything to do with my music.', 'Norah Jones', 'music'),
(11175, 'Maybe I\'m genetically more inclined to music - but the music I make is so far removed from Indian classical music. I grew up in Texas!', 'Norah Jones', 'music'),
(11176, 'I just want to make my music and I want it to stand on its own.', 'Norah Jones', 'music'),
(11177, 'I don\'t actually have a lot of discipline. I\'ve worked hard at music. But I feel like you know I felt like kind of natural at it. I always had a knack for it.', 'Norah Jones', 'music'),
