(11187, 'Our music\'s kind of about taking something ugly and making it beautiful.', 'Jerry Cantrell', 'music'),
(11188, 'I\'ve never intended to be controversial but it\'s very easy to be controversial in pop music because nobody ever is.', 'Steven Patrick Morrissey', 'music'),
(11189, 'I can sing very comfortably from my vantage point because a lot of the music was about a loss of innocence there\'s innocence contained in you but there\'s also innocence in the process of being lost.', 'Bruce Springsteen', 'music'),
(11190, 'If somebody for some reason for music or for movie becomes famous it\'s because they have something something special.', 'Roberto Cavalli', 'music'),
(11191, 'Pop music has progressed.', 'Steven Patrick Morrissey', 'music'),
(11192, 'I always wanted my music to influence the life you were living emotionally - with your family your lover your wife and at a certain point with your children.', 'Bruce Springsteen', 'music'),
(11193, 'I find that it isn\'t wise to attempt to judge people on their public persona and even on the music they make. Because I\'ve met so many people whose music I cannot stand and they\'re very nice. At the same time I\'ve met people whose music I\'ve loved and the', 'Steven Patrick Morrissey', 'music'),
(11194, 'I think that is what film and art and music do they can work as a map of sorts for your feelings.', 'Bruce Springsteen', 'music'),
(11195, 'I think there are unseen powers who don\'t want pop music to be anything other than glorified Madonnas.', 'Steven Patrick Morrissey', 'music'),
(11196, 'And whether you\'re drawn to gospel music or church music or honky-tonk music it informs your character and it informs your talent.', 'Bruce Springsteen', 'music'),
(11197, 'Music can affect for good or ill the body as well as the mind.', 'Tomas Luis de Victoria', 'music'),
(11198, 'I\'ve only been to Ireland once and I felt I would wake up with voices in my head almost like music and that if I were a songwriter I would be very inspired.', 'Steven Patrick Morrissey', 'music'),
(11199, 'Hearing my songs in public freaks me out a bit. There was one restaurant I really liked in L.A. but I had to stop going there when they started playing my music. It felt kinda awkward.', 'Fiona Apple', 'music'),
(11200, 'One and the same thing can at the same time be good bad and indifferent e.g. music is good to the melancholy bad to those who mourn and neither good nor bad to the deaf.', 'Baruch Spinoza', 'music'),
