(12245, 'Cat: a pygmy lion who loves mice hates dogs and patronizes human beings.', 'Oliver Herford', 'pet'),
(12246, 'The trouble with a kitten is that eventually it becomes a cat.', 'Ogden Nash', 'pet'),
(12247, 'Cats are intended to teach us that not everything in nature has a function.', 'Garrison Keillor', 'pet'),
(12248, 'Way down deep we\'re all motivated by the same urges. Cats have the courage to live by them.', 'Jim Davis', 'pet'),
(12249, 'Dogs are our link to paradise. They don\'t know evil or jealousy or discontent.', 'Milan Kundera', 'pet'),
(12250, 'Don\'t accept your dog\'s admiration as conclusive evidence that you are wonderful.', 'Ann Landers', 'pet'),
