(12259, 'We\'ve begun to long for the pitter-patter of little feet - so we bought a dog. Well it\'s cheaper and you get more feet.', 'Rita Rudner', 'pet'),
(12260, 'Cats are rather delicate creatures and they are subject to a good many different ailments but I have never heard of one who suffered from insomnia.', 'Joseph Wood Krutch', 'pet'),
