(12304, 'When a guy tells me I\'m cute it\'s not something desirable. Cute is more like what you want your pet to be.', 'Natalie Portman', 'pet'),
(12305, 'A lover tries to stand in well with the pet dog of the house.', 'Moliere', 'pet'),
(12306, 'Teach your children how to behave with animals. Adopt a pet. Don\'t go buy one. Please. That\'s a sin. Let\'s get these puppy mills out of business.', 'Shelley Morrison', 'pet'),
(12307, 'I don\'t have pet peeves I have whole kennels of irritation.', 'Whoopi Goldberg', 'pet'),
(12308, 'I really liked the snake that breaks out of the cage in the beginning of the movie. I saw it in real life and it was really cool. Really big and fat. The owls are cool as well but you can\'t really pet them.', 'Tom Felton', 'pet'),
(12309, 'There\'s kind of a toll you have to pay with a cat if you don\'t pet her for 10 minutes she\'ll bother you for six hours.', 'Scott Adams', 'pet'),
(12310, 'Vinyl is the real deal. I\'ve always felt like until you buy the vinyl record you don\'t really own the album. And it\'s not just me or a little pet thing or some kind of retro romantic thing from the past. It is still alive.', 'Jack White', 'pet'),
(12311, 'I\'m scared to death of being poor. It\'s like a fat girl who loses 500 pounds but is always fat inside. I grew up poor and will always feel poor inside. It\'s my pet paranoia.', 'Cher', 'pet'),
(12312, 'My pet peeve and my goal in life is to somehow get an adjective for \'integrity\' in the dictionary. \'Truthful\' doesn\'t really cover it or \'genuine.\' It should be like \'integritus.\'', 'Rashida Jones', 'pet'),
(12313, 'My parents used to take me to the pet department and tell me it was a zoo.', 'Billy Connolly', 'pet'),
(12314, 'We created a line of pet food called Nutrish that\'s made to human standards and 100 percent of the proceeds go to animal rescue. One of our top-tier donors is the ASPCA and they help us challenge animal shelters all across the country to get more animals ', 'Rachael Ray', 'pet'),
(12315, 'It\'s a little known fact that one in three family pets gets lost during its lifetime and approximately 9 million pets enter shelters each year. That\'s why it\'s a wonderful thing to get your pet microchipped and registered with your contact information bec', 'Betty White', 'pet'),
(12316, 'I used to have this little mouse. I buy birds from the pet store and I let them go.', 'Ziggy Marley', 'pet'),
(12317, 'We all know the stories about the Human Rights Act... about the illegal immigrant who cannot be deported because and I am not making this up he had a pet cat.', 'Theresa May', 'pet'),
(12318, 'Every time I decide I want a child I get another pet. I have 3 dogs 13 birds and 3 horses what does that tell you?', 'Alyssa Milano', 'pet'),
(12319, 'No one ever pretended that shopping for anything is a rational experience. If it were would there be Fluffernutter? Laceless sneakers? Porkpie hats? Would the Chia Pet even exist?', 'Jeffrey Kluger', 'pet'),
(12320, 'When you want a break from dogs and you take them to the kennel to the stars no one thinks you\'re a bad pet owner. But when you have kids you can\'t drop them off for three weeks without someone calling Child Protective Services!', 'Gabrielle Union', 'pet'),
(12321, 'A pet store is a celebration of dogs\' existence and an explosion of options. About cats a pet store seems to say \'Here we couldn\'t think of anything else.\' Cats are the Hanukkah of the animal world in this way. They are feted quietly and happily by a mino', 'Sloane Crosley', 'pet'),
(12322, 'I love animals and feel very strongly that people should not be allowed to buy a pet if they are not able to look after it.', 'Kirsty Gallacher', 'pet'),
(12323, 'Our pets rely on us entirely for their nutrition. So if you\'re making your own judgments that could lead to a mistake. At the same time we have more control over our pet\'s diet than we do with our children or with ourselves so your vet can tell you what i', 'Alison Sweeney', 'pet'),
(12324, 'Humans should always exercise and watch what they eat. So with your pet make sure they get enough exercise make sure they\'re getting fed at the same time every day and getting the nutrition they need. And make sure they get a lot of love and attention you', 'Alison Sweeney', 'pet'),
(12325, 'One of my pet peeves is that sometimes the talents of my band get overlooked because and it was the same problem that Frank Zappa had with a lot of groups that use humor people don\'t realize there\'s a lot of craft behind the comedy.', 'Al Yankovic', 'pet'),
(12326, 'In their heyday the Pet Shop Boys were the Interpol of the Eighties dressing up to sing really weird pop songs about lust and loneliness in the big city. They\'re low-pro now not retro-worshipped in the manner of Depeche Mode New Order or The Cure but you ', 'Rob Sheffield', 'pet'),
(12327, 'It doesn\'t work if the bad guys kill his mother\'s uncle\'s friend\'s neighbor\'s pet dog. You\'ve got to make the stakes high.', 'Steven Seagal', 'pet'),
(12328, 'Environmentalists hate sprawl - except when it comes to the size of their expansive pet legislation on Capitol Hill.', 'Michelle Malkin', 'pet'),
(12329, 'I have a lot of plants and fish and a pet lizard and Venus flytraps. I have a whole ecosystem in my room like a running waterfall and different lights and sensors set on digital timers.', 'Chris Pratt', 'pet'),
(12330, 'I have a pet lizard named Puff five goldfish - named Pinky Brain Jowels Pearl and Sandy an oscar fish named Chef two pacus an albino African frog named Whitey a bonsai tree four Venus flytraps a fruit fly farm and sea monkeys.', 'Chris Pratt', 'pet'),
(12331, 'Truth be told ginormous portions have become a pet peeve of mine.', 'Hal Sparks', 'pet'),
(12332, 'I brought a Border Collie back home to Vancouver from Wales - where some of my ancestors are from - and needed to challenge him in other ways than just being my pet. So I investigated sheep herding and took a few lessons and decided I was probably learnin', 'Jane Siberry', 'pet'),
(12333, 'Packing is my pet hate.', 'Seal', 'pet'),
(12334, 'I\'d say the best is when I was in Africa I saw a hippo in a house. Someone had a pet hippo. And they\'re meant to be one of the most dangerous animals on the planet and they had one that was sort of just wandering in and out of their house just sort of roa', 'Karl Pilkington', 'pet'),
(12335, 'I\'m not about to go out and buy a snake for a pet. I mean I may have faced a few fears but I\'m not insane.', 'Kristin Davis', 'pet'),
(12336, 'I have the same pet peeve as Anderson Cooper which is bare feet in public. I hate it. It so grosses me out especially in New York. Oh my God New York in the summer with people and their feet in their sandals and their flip-flops like get it away!', 'Busy Philipps', 'pet'),
(12337, 'I try not to wear anything I have to fidget with - there\'s nothing worse than wearing something and pulling down the hem and re-adjusting the top. My pet hate is when girls wear those strapless dresses and spend the whole night yanking them up.', 'Sophie Ellis-Bextor', 'pet'),
(12338, 'My idea of a perfect pet is a really really big dog! Huge!', 'Emily VanCamp', 'pet'),
(12339, 'I\'ve been lucky. I\'ve made films that I really like. It\'s been a combination of what comes to me and what I choose. I\'ve gone after lots of things that I didn\'t get pet projects that everybody ends up chasing after. Really you\'re lucky if you get anything', 'Hope Davis', 'pet'),
(12340, 'If you have a deep-seated need to be loved and admired every day you shouldn\'t be in politics. You should go work at a pet store.', 'Michael Nutter', 'pet'),
(12341, 'Pet lovers know that animals sometimes understand us better than we do and the annals of human sin and desire provide plenty of stories to drive the point home.', 'Tony Snow', 'pet'),
(12342, 'My parents were very permissive when it came to animals. As long as we earned the money to buy them and built whatever structure it was they were going to live in we could have any kind of pet we wanted. They would have let us have a rhinoceros if we coul', 'Maggie Stiefvater', 'pet'),
(12343, 'There are people all over the world who like to write fan letters in the voice of their pet: \'Hello my name is Fifi and I\'m a labrador and I think you\'re great. Paw paw!\'', 'Rebecca Hall', 'pet'),
(12344, 'To me a cat is an easy pet they don\'t need any spoiling or looking after.', 'Karl Pilkington', 'pet'),
(12345, 'I\'ve teamed up with PetSmart Charities to celebrate the five million homeless pets who\'ve found homes through their in-store adoption centers and to spread the word about how we can work together to save millions more pets\' lives and ultimately end pet ho', 'Josh Duhamel', 'pet'),
(12346, 'It is one of my pet hates when I see players who have agents who do everything for them. They don\'t know how to set up their own bank accounts they don\'t know what they are spending their money on and they can\'t make their own decisions.', 'Gary Neville', 'pet'),
(12347, 'The government needs to help those in need but members of Congress shouldn\'t take advantage of the situation and use a national tragedy as an opportunity to spend taxpayer dollars on their pet projects.', 'Chris Chocola', 'pet'),
(12348, 'I had a big Akita Yoshi who was fabulous. I loved him. We lost him when he was 12 and I\'ve never been able to replace him. Normally most people lose a pet and get another and keep going on. But it just felt wrong to me it felt disloyal.', 'Robert Crais', 'pet'),
(12349, 'I could probably give you a list of a dozen pet peeves I have about my own physicality and why I couldn\'t get a second date.', 'Zachary Levi', 'pet'),
(12350, 'Our cat is kind dove shellfish and thinks the world is hers She finds a comfy spot and then we pet turtle sheep purrs.', 'Brian P. Cleary', 'pet'),
(12351, 'You can get too bogged down in technology and you can sort of forget what it is you were trying to do. And with the Pet Shop Boys it\'s primarily about the songs it\'s about song writing.', 'Chris Lowe', 'pet'),
(12352, 'We all have our pet things that we like to get religious about.', 'Max Cannon', 'pet'),
(12353, 'I am an enthusiast but not a crank in the sense that I have some pet theories as to the proper construction of a flying machine. I wish to avail myself of all that is already known and then if possible add my mite to help on the future worker who will att', 'Wilbur Wright', 'pet'),
(12354, 'We are telling veterans they must sacrifice to pay for the pet projects and contracts to campaign donors of powerful members of Congress.', 'Nick Lampson', 'pet'),
(12355, 'Those who wish to pet and baby wild animals \'love\' them. But those who respect their natures and wish to let them live normal lives love them more.', 'Edwin Way Teale', 'pet'),
(12356, 'There are things that I invented - the creaky geriatric robot that is always grumpy for example or the little wheelie guy he\'s not in the Hasbro lore. But kids love that stuff - this little guy as a pet on a chain. They gravitate towards it.', 'Michael Bay', 'pet'),
(12357, 'I have some road rage inside of me. Traffic especially in L.A. is a pet peeve of mine.', 'Katie Holmes', 'pet'),
(12358, 'I have a Lab it\'s fun to hang out and hike with the dog people come up to him and pet him it\'s fun.', 'George Eads', 'pet'),
(12359, 'I heard that Jesus had a pet dinosaur. Evolution must be a myth then.', 'John Bacon', 'pet'),
(12360, 'Gypsy was the name my brother gave a pet turtle he had. I always thought it was so peculiar.', 'Joel Hodgson', 'pet'),
(12361, 'Crabbed and obscure definitions are of no use beyond a narrow circle of students of whom probably every one has a pet one of his own.', 'Frederick Pollock', 'pet'),
(12362, 'I was in New York and I walked into this pet store and came out with a dog.', 'Beverley Mitchell', 'pet'),
(12363, 'Pet me touch me love me that\'s what I get when I perform. That\'s when I\'m really getting what I want.', 'Connie Stevens', 'pet'),
(12364, 'I think there\'s something great and generic about goldfish. They\'re everybody\'s first pet.', 'Paul Rudd', 'pet'),
(12365, 'My biggest pet peeve are just girls who go to sports bars who have no intention on caring what teams are playing like they\'re looking for just a night out. That drives me more crazy than anything else. Like don\'t pretend to be a sports fan.', 'Jerry Ferrara', 'pet'),
(12366, 'It\'s true you can never eat a pet you name. And anyway it would be like a ventriloquist eating his dummy.', 'Alexander Theroux', 'pet'),
(12367, 'Pet stores just sell their animals.', 'Booboo Stewart', 'pet'),
(12368, 'I have this pet thing about how global communications are moving so fast now throwing information at you making everything available to you and yet I feel it\'s leaving us more and more isolated.', 'Mike Rutherford', 'pet'),
