(12585, 'It seems to me that socialists today can preserve their position in academic economics merely by the pretense that the differences are entirely moral questions about which science cannot decide.', 'Friedrich August von Hayek', 'science'),
(12586, 'Books are the carriers of civilization. Without books history is silent literature dumb science crippled thought and speculation at a standstill.', 'Barbara Tuchman', 'science'),
