(12653, 'I wasn\'t with Joseph but I believe him. My faith did not come to me through science and I will not permit so-called science to destroy it.', 'Thomas S. Monson', 'science'),
(12654, 'The most watched programme on the BBC after the news is probably \'Doctor Who.\' What has happened is that science fiction has been subsumed into modern literature. There are grandparents out there who speak Klingon who are quite capable of holding down a j', 'Terry Pratchett', 'science'),
(12655, 'Physics does not change the nature of the world it studies and no science of behavior can change the essential nature of man even though both sciences yield technologies with a vast power to manipulate the subject matters.', 'Pope Paul VI', 'science'),
