(12664, 'That which today calls itself science gives us more and more information and indigestible glut of information and less and less understanding.', 'Edward Abbey', 'science'),
(12665, 'Man masters nature not by force but by understanding. This is why science has succeeded where magic failed: because it has looked for no spell to cast over nature.', 'Jacob Bronowski', 'science'),
