(13301, 'When I did \'Battlestar Galactica\' it was the first time I really understood science fiction. That was a very political drama but set in spaceships so people didn\'t really take it seriously. But some really fascinating things were explored in that.', 'Michelle Forbes', 'science'),
(13302, 'Science consists exactly of those forms of knowledge that can be verified and duplicated by anybody.', 'Seth Lloyd', 'science'),
